t and a view of Madison's Capitol available for rent as a private office.](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDI0IiBoZWlnaHQ9Ijc2OCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDEwMjQgNzY4Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n## Offices for Rent\n\n$850-$2,000/month", "char_len": 2231, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::41", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 41, "text": "for rent as a private office.](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDI0IiBoZWlnaHQ9Ijc2OCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDEwMjQgNzY4Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n## Offices for Rent\n\n$850-$2,000/month\n\nWant to be part of the vibrant 100state community but need or want a more private office space for you and your team?\n\nGood news, we also have opportunities to rent office space.\n\nPlease send us an email at hello@100state.com and we’d be happy to discuss helping you and your team evaluate 100state as a home for your startup and give you a tour of the space.\n\nIf you’d like to learn more, come down and cowork for a day (first time is our treat), and/or setup a tour, please email us at hello@100state.com.\n\n## Member Amenities\n\n### Office Services\n\nWe offer free printing, copying, scanning, and shredding. You can also receive business mail at 100state.\n\n### 24/7 Keycard Access\n\nMembers get 24/7 access to the shared space and can access all normal amenities at any time.\n\n### Coffee and Tea\n\nWe keep the pantry stocked with a variety of teas and provide a coffee maker for members to use. Our kitchenette includes a refrigerator, toaster oven, and microwave.\n\n### Reservable Meeting Rooms\n\nWe have several reservable conference rooms with whiteboards and projectors or TVs. Our largest conference room can accommodate 10 guests. Members can reserve these spaces for individual use or to meet with clients, partners, and colleagues.\n\n### Phone Booths\n\nOur shared space area includes two phone booths that offer privacy for phone calls and virtual meetings and keep the shared office quiet and productive for those around you.\n\n### Secure Indoor Bike Parking\n\nOur secure bike storage room is conveniently located next door to the main entrance. You don’t have to walk your bike through the halls or up the elevator or navigate any steps. Sudden rain storm? Leave your bike behind and pick it up later with 24/7 keycard access.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/100resources\n\n# 100resources\n\n## Organizations and Accelerators\n\n**BioForward**\n\nOrganization advocates for the life sciences industry in Wisconsin and features regular events and receptions.\n\n**Capital Entrepreneurs**", "char_len": 2272, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::42", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 42, "text": "and pick it up later with 24/7 keycard access.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/100resources\n\n# 100resources\n\n## Organizations and Accelerators\n\n**BioForward**\n\nOrganization advocates for the life sciences industry in Wisconsin and features regular events and receptions.\n\n**Capital Entrepreneurs**\n\nAn association for Madison-area entrepreneurs who meet regularly.\n\n**Doyenne Group**\n\nSupports women entrepreneurs in the Madison region through mentoring and networking opportunities.\n\n**Score**\n\nFree and confidential mentoring along with low-cost or no-cost business training, seminars, workshops, and numerous tools and templates.\n\n**Gener8tor**\n\nA startup accelerator for companies in Madison and Milwaukee.\n\n**Law and Entrepreneurship Clinic**\n\nStart-ups receive advice on legal issues. Online application.\n\n**Madison College – Center for Entrepreneurship**\n\nSign up for workshops, get advice from experienced entrepreneurs, or compete in a business planning contest.\n\n**University Research Park**\n\nFlexible leases and space in University Research Park or the Metro Innovation Center.\n\n**Wisconsin Angel Network**\n\nTracks deal flow in the state of Wisconsin and connects entrepreneurs to investors.\n\n**Wisconsin Entrepreneurs’ Network**\n\nOne-on-one advising, resources and assistance with SBIR/STTR grant applications. Operates across Wisconsin.\n\n**Wisconsin Technology Council**\n\nSupports the formation/growth of high-tech companies. Organizes the Entrepreneurs’ Conference and Early Stage Symposium.\\\n\n**Wisconsin Women’s Business Initiative Corporation**\n\nProvides education and financing to Wisconsin’s entrepreneurs and small business owners.\n\n**MAGNET**\n\nMagnet was founded in 2004 with a mission to provide Young Professionals with opportunities to develop **socially,** **professionally**, and **civically** in the Madison area.\n\n## Coworking Spaces\n\n**100state**\n100state is a nonprofit organization. Our mission is to provide a home for entrepreneurs, problem solvers, and creatives. Located in downtown Madison.\n\n**Horizon Coworking**\nLocated in Murfie’s offices on the third floor of 7 North Pinckney, they offer shared desk and counter space, a limited number of reserved desks, and other amenities.", "char_len": 2216, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::43", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 43, "text": "mission is to provide a home for entrepreneurs, problem solvers, and creatives. Located in downtown Madison.\n\n**Horizon Coworking**\nLocated in Murfie’s offices on the third floor of 7 North Pinckney, they offer shared desk and counter space, a limited number of reserved desks, and other amenities.\n\n**Sector67**\nSector67 is a non-profit collaborative space in Madison, WI dedicated to providing an environment to learn, teach, work-on, build, and create next generation technology.\n\nStarting Block\n\n## Events\n\n**Forward Festival**\n\nProvides a mix of talks, panels, and networking opportunities over 10 days celebrating innovation and entrepreneurship.\n\n**Hi-Tech Happy Hour**\n\nMonthly networking for Madison’s high-tech community—no pre-registration, no speakers, no format, no fees.\n\n**WARF Entrepreneurons**\n\nEntrepreneurons brings together thought leaders from across the country and our own backyard to exchange perspectives on core topics ranging from identifying an opportunity to building a startup team to financing and beyond.\n\nMadson Downtowners\n\nThe Downtowners are an informal social group of people who live, work or enjoy Downtown Madison. We do this through monthly happy hour events connecting people to resources\n\n## UW-Madison Resources\n\n**Wisconsin Alumni Research Foundation**\n\nGuidance and support for faculty, staff and students with assessment, patenting and licensing.\n\n**UW Madison Entrepreneur Resource Page**\n\n**Small Business Resource Center**\n\n## Competitions\n\n**NEST Software Competition**\n\nDevelop a new software application. Win $5,000.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/faq\n\n# Frequently Asked Questions\n\nBelow you will find answers to many common questions (faq) you might have about the 100state coworking space.  Please feel free to reach out to us if your question wasn’t answered.\n\n![Frequently Asked Questions](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDMwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)\n\n### History\n\n**Why is the name 100state when you’re not actually at 100state Street?**\n\n100State was the original address and location above Ian’s Pizza on State Street when 100state started back in 2013.", "char_len": 2274, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::44", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 44, "text": "History\n\n**Why is the name 100state when you’re not actually at 100state Street?**\n\n100State was the original address and location above Ian’s Pizza on State Street when 100state started back in 2013.\n\n**Is 100state a for-profit or a non-profit organization?**\n\n100state is setup as a 501 (c) 3 non-profit organization.\n\n**How many locations has 100state had?**\n\nFour (4). 100 State Street (4th floor above Ian’s), 30 West Mifflin St (on the capital square above Coopers), 316 West Washington Avenue, and our current location, 17 South Fairchild Street.\n\n### Utilities\n\n**Where are the paper towels and toilet paper?**\n\n* Toiletry items including soap, should we ever run out, can be found next to the fridge under the red cabinet. There may also be a stash under the counter in the respective bathrooms. These are on auto-replenish from Amazon and scheduled to replenish every month.\n\n**Coffee machines?**\n\n1. Where are grounds kept? In the cabinet on the far left in the kitchen.\n2. How to order more coffee? 100state does not have an ongoing coffee service. Coffee grounds are provided by the organization through partnerships with local roasters and members who want to bring in their own coffee. If you would like to provide a month of coffee for 100state, please email hello@100state.com subject line: Coffee\n\n**Where are the lights for the building?**\n\n* Most lights are on the walls near the doors. The two sets of master lights are to the left of the elevator and to the right of the phone booth closest to the Pressure Cooker (office room).\n\n**How to change temperature?**\n\n1. There are two thermostats on the floor\n2. One is in the Government Oversight room, the other is on the wall near the printers. Please do not change the thermostats without contacting the others near you in the space or the 100state staff.\n\n### Parking\n\nFor full day visits, we recommend that you park in the ramp on the corner of Fairchild and East Main Street.\n\nFor shorter visits, there are 25 minute, 1 hour and 2 hour parking meters in front of the building on Fairchild St and along East Main Street and East Henry Street.\n\nMeters are enforced 8am-6pm Monday through Saturday.\n\n### Membership", "char_len": 2184, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::45", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 45, "text": "in the ramp on the corner of Fairchild and East Main Street.\n\nFor shorter visits, there are 25 minute, 1 hour and 2 hour parking meters in front of the building on Fairchild St and along East Main Street and East Henry Street.\n\nMeters are enforced 8am-6pm Monday through Saturday.\n\n### Membership\n\n**How can I change or make payment arrangements?**\n\n* Payments are handled through Moonclerk and Stripe. Please email hello@100state.com if you have questions or concerns about membership payments. Alternatively there is a link at the bottom of your monthly email receipt where you can update your payment information.\n\n**Can I bring a non-member?**\n\n* Absolutely, we encourage you to bring friends and co-workers from time to time. If someone wants to become a regular user of the space, we would encourage them to pursue regular membership.\n\n**Who do I contact if I have an issue?**\n\n* The quickest way to get a response is to ping the #general channel in Slack. Slack is a great app to have open throughout the day to keep in touch with coworkers and abreast of things going on in the space (treats, events, questions, games….etc)\n* For additional inquiries, please contact joseph@100state.com. If your matter is urgent, you may contact Joseph on his cell phone via call or text at 608-609-6716.\n\n**What do I do if I am locked out?**\n\n* Ping the Slack channel as a first step. Also a good idea to get a cell phone number from a coworker or two just in case. Joseph can be reached at his cell phone # above.\n\n**How do I reserve a conference room or check if they’re free?**\n\n* Please check LiquidSpace to reserve a conference room. Conference rooms are free to use for regular (pro) members.\n\n### Emergency\n\n**Northwest (out the elevator and to the right) and southeast corners (behind Kyle’s desk) of the floor both have fire exits. Please familiarize yourself with the closest available exit.**\n\n### Additional Resources\n\n**1. SLACK**", "char_len": 1936, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::46", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 46, "text": "rooms are free to use for regular (pro) members.\n\n### Emergency\n\n**Northwest (out the elevator and to the right) and southeast corners (behind Kyle’s desk) of the floor both have fire exits. Please familiarize yourself with the closest available exit.**\n\n### Additional Resources\n\n**1. SLACK**\n\nThe primary business, social and community communication platform used by 100state. We make the most of channels organized by topic. Get started following the prompts in the “#new-member” channel. If you have any questions about 100state or its communal space, ask within slack for the best immediate response. If there is a more personal question you want to ask a staff member, email hello@100state.com.\n\n**2. LIQUIDSPACE**\n\nReal-time scheduling system for our three conference rooms.\n\nhttps://liquidspace.com/My/Liquidspace\n\n3. PRIVATE FACEBOOK GROUP\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/groups/100state\n\n## Have a question not listed?\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/founders-circle-ignite-the-ultimate-entrepreneurial-bootcamp-at-100state\n\n# Founders Circle Ignite: The Ultimate Entrepreneurial Bootcamp at 100state\n\n![Entrepreneur Bootcamp](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9Ijg4NyIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDEwMDAgODg3Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\nPosted on February 9, 2025\n\nMadison’s startup scene is heating up, and if you’re an entrepreneur ready to take your business idea to the next level, **Founders Circle Ignite** is where your journey begins! Powered by The Network for Health, Technology, and Innovation (NHTI) in partnership with **100state**, this **game-changing 8-week bootcamp** is designed to give entrepreneurs the **tools, knowledge, and network** they need to turn ideas into thriving businesses.\n\n### **What is Founders Circle Ignite?**\n\nIt’s more than just a bootcamp—it’s a **launchpad for dreamers, innovators, and go-getters**. Over the course of 8 weeks, participants will dive deep into **business fundamentals, pitching strategies, goal setting, and startup growth tactics**—all while building a powerful network of **mentors, investors, and fellow entrepreneurs**.", "char_len": 2198, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::47", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 47, "text": "a **launchpad for dreamers, innovators, and go-getters**. Over the course of 8 weeks, participants will dive deep into **business fundamentals, pitching strategies, goal setting, and startup growth tactics**—all while building a powerful network of **mentors, investors, and fellow entrepreneurs**.\n\n📅 **Session Dates:** March 3rd – May 1st, 2025\n📍 **Location:** Virtual (Tuesdays) & In-Person at 100state (Thursdays)\n\n### **What You’ll Gain from This Bootcamp**\n\n🔥 **Expert-Led Workshops** – Learn from industry pros who have been in your shoes and succeeded.\n\n🚀 **Hands-On Business Development** – Get practical, actionable insights tailored to your startup’s needs.\n\n🤝 **High-Impact Networking** – Connect with investors, mentors, and like-minded entrepreneurs who can fuel your growth.\n\n💡 **Pitch Perfect Training** – Refine your business pitch and gain the confidence to sell your vision.\n\n### **Bootcamp Breakdown**\n\n* **Tuesdays (Virtual)** – Foundational business concepts, startup strategy, and entrepreneurial mindset development.\n* **Thursdays (In-Person at 100state)** – Advanced workshops, pitch practice, and interactive mentorship.\n\n*Bonus:* A **final showcase event** where participants pitch their business ideas to an audience of investors and business leaders! 🎤💡\n\n### **Who Should Apply?**\n\nWhether you’re a **first-time founder, an aspiring entrepreneur, or a business owner looking to scale**, Founders Circle Ignite is built to help you **level up and execute your vision with clarity and confidence**.\n\n### **Secure Your Spot!**\n\nSpots are limited, and applications are already rolling in! Don’t miss your chance to be part of **Madison’s most dynamic entrepreneur bootcamp**.\n\n👉 **Apply now at** **100state.com/founders-circle-ignite** and take the first step towards building your dream business! 🚀\n\nPrevious Post\n\n100state: Madison’s Entrepreneurs hub to Ignite Dreams\n\n## Recent Posts", "char_len": 1912, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
