iel Guerra Jr.​\n\nExecutive Director\n\n**Daniel G. Guerra Jr. – Entrepreneur, Venture Builder & Economic Development Leader**", "char_len": 1997, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::63", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 63, "text": "Daniel Guerra Jr.​\n\nExecutive Director\n\n**Daniel G. Guerra Jr. – Entrepreneur, Venture Builder & Economic Development Leader**\n\nDaniel G. Guerra Jr. is the founder and CEO of Altus, Inc., a venture studio dedicated to building scalable, investable companies in healthtech, fintech, and edtech, with a focus on underrepresented founders. Passionate about innovation and economic equality, he has spent his career identifying and supporting businesses that drive both financial and social impact. His commitment to creating opportunities for diverse entrepreneurs is deeply personal, shaped by his own experiences—including witnessing the challenges his immigrant father faced in the healthcare system. This fuels his drive to advance solutions that improve healthcare and empower small businesses.\n\nHe is also an Inaugural Fellow of the Stanford Latino Entrepreneurship Initiative (SLEI), a national program focused on scaling Latino-owned businesses.\n\nBeyond his entrepreneurial ventures, Daniel has played a key role in community and economic development. As a both a member and serving as Chair of Madison’s Community Development Authority (CDA) from 2011 to 2019, he led redevelopment efforts, affordable housing initiatives, and the management of Section 8 housing, supporting over 1,800 low-income residents.\n\nHis leadership extends across multiple organizations, Daniel previously served on the board of directors for the Greater Madison Chamber of Commerce, Latino Professional Association, and BetterInvesting/National Association Investor Corporation, Inc.\n\nCurrently, Mr. Guerra serves as a board member and treasure for Wisconsin Latino Chamber of Commerce, where he is a champion for Latino business growth and financial empowerment,\n\nVice-Chair for Working Capital for Community Needs (WCCN) a $17 million nonprofit organization that partners with microlenders In Mexico, Central and South America, and board member for 100State, Inc. an entrepreneurial community, the Wisconsin Environmental Initiative (WEI), and Small Business for America’s Future a national small business advocacy organization.", "char_len": 2112, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::64", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 64, "text": "nonprofit organization that partners with microlenders In Mexico, Central and South America, and board member for 100State, Inc. an entrepreneurial community, the Wisconsin Environmental Initiative (WEI), and Small Business for America’s Future a national small business advocacy organization.\n\nDaniel continues to shape policy, investment strategies, and development initiatives that drive both entrepreneurship and sustainability. His expertise in business operations, public-private partnerships, and venture strategy makes him a trusted advisor in scaling businesses, securing funding, and driving economic transformation.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/giovanni-a-aleman-sotelo\n\n![Giovanni A. Aleman Sotelo](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDgwMCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n### Giovanni A. Aleman Sotelo\n\nGiovanni A. Aleman Sotelo is a business and economic development professional with a strong background in accounting, operations, and entrepreneurship. Passionate about helping small businesses thrive, he provides financial expertise, operational support, and strategic marketing solutions that drive sustainable growth.\nAs Director of Operations at Altus, Inc., Giovanni oversees business implementation, financial management, and strategy. He is also actively involved with The Network for Health, Technology, and Innovation (NHTI), where they tackle economic development. At NHTI, he builds relationships with entrepreneurs, provides direct mentorship, leads business courses in their free Business Ignite program, and collaborates with organizations committed to business, professional, and economic development. His focus is on creating impactful programs and partnerships that empower local businesses.", "char_len": 1886, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::65", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 65, "text": "entrepreneurs, provides direct mentorship, leads business courses in their free Business Ignite program, and collaborates with organizations committed to business, professional, and economic development. His focus is on creating impactful programs and partnerships that empower local businesses.\n\nWith expertise in accounting, tax preparation, and financial strategy, Giovanni has worked with organizations such as Wegner CPA, Artful Home, Center for Community Stewardship (C4CS), and Verhelst CPA. His experience spans business finance, operational efficiency, and process automation, helping companies streamline workflows and make informed, data-driven decisions.\nBeyond finance, Giovanni has a deep entrepreneurial background in marketing and media. A self-taught videographer and brand strategist, he launched his own consulting firm to help businesses strengthen their brand presence through digital storytelling. His firsthand experience as a business owner gives him unique insight into the challenges entrepreneurs face, allowing him to offer practical, results-oriented solutions.\n\nCommitted to fostering economic mobility and collaboration, Giovanni works to develop resources that support business growth, scalability, and long-term success. Whether through financial strategy, operational consulting, marketing guidance, or other business education, his mission is to equip entrepreneurs with the tools they need to thrive.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/joseph-dahari\n\n![Joseph Dahari](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDgwMCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n### Joseph Dahari", "char_len": 1751, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::66", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 66, "text": "Dahari](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDgwMCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n### Joseph Dahari\n\nJoseph Dahari was part of 100state’s founding team in 2013, serving as the organization’s first Executive Director and helping establish the coworking space and startup community from the ground up. Since his time leading 100state, Joseph has helped grow startups including Fetch, GroceryKey, and Birdzi, while always finding time to mentor founders and support community programs. With more than 15 years of startup and go-to-market experience, he spends his time helping early-stage teams find product–market fit and build repeatable growth. Joseph holds degrees in Finance and Real Estate from the University of Wisconsin–Madison. He’s also a dedicated runner with a current streak of over 1,100 consecutive days.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/nick-myers\n\n![Nick Myers](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDgwMCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n### Nick Myers\n\nNick Myers is the Director of AI Innovation at Recovery.com, one of Wisconsin’s fastest-growing companies helping people find the best path to recovery through a global network of treatment providers. He joined Recovery.com after its 2025 acquisition of RedFox AI, the award-winning Madison-based healthcare AI startup he co-founded, which built conversational AI tools for home lab testing and medical devices.", "char_len": 1683, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::67", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 67, "text": "people find the best path to recovery through a global network of treatment providers. He joined Recovery.com after its 2025 acquisition of RedFox AI, the award-winning Madison-based healthcare AI startup he co-founded, which built conversational AI tools for home lab testing and medical devices.\n\nHe serves on the boards of the Wisconsin Technology Council and the Wisconsin Startup Coalition. He is also a nationally recognized Advocate with Blood Cancer United, meeting with lawmakers in Washington, D.C. to advance research and patient support. A longtime voice in AI, Nick has delivered TEDx and international keynotes on AI, conversational tech, and data privacy. His work has earned recognition, including In Business Madison’s *40 Under 40* and *Best of Madison Business* awards, and has been featured in *PR Daily*, the *Wisconsin State Journal*, and other outlets.\n\nHe holds a B.S. in Communication and Business Administration from the University of Wisconsin–Stevens Point and a certificate in Open Innovation from Harvard Business School.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/lou-elson\n\n![Lou Elson](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDgwMCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n### Lou Elson\n\nLou Elson has called Madison home for more than 20 years, and he can’t imagine building his life or businesses anywhere else. Before stepping into real estate, Lou owned and operated a commercial janitorial supply company, an experience that strengthened his entrepreneurial drive and deepened his appreciation for serving local businesses.\n\nIn 2018, Lou followed a long-held passion and became a licensed real estate broker. Today, he leads a dedicated team of real estate professionals who share his mission: to simplify the buying and selling process so clients feel confident, supported, and excited. Helping people achieve their dreams of homeownership continues to be one of Lou’s greatest motivators.", "char_len": 2063, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::68", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 68, "text": "estate broker. Today, he leads a dedicated team of real estate professionals who share his mission: to simplify the buying and selling process so clients feel confident, supported, and excited. Helping people achieve their dreams of homeownership continues to be one of Lou’s greatest motivators.\n\nEntrepreneurship has always been at the heart of Lou’s journey, and that passion naturally led him to 100state. He is honored to serve on the board, where he looks forward to supporting Madison’s vibrant community of innovators, sharing ideas, and helping the next generation of entrepreneurs thrive.\n\nFor Lou, 100state is more than a workspace—it’s a place to strengthen connections, spark creativity, and grow the entrepreneurial spirit across Madison.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/andy-friske\n\n![Andy Friske](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDgwMCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n### Andy Friske\n\nAndy Friske is a marketing professional and community builder based in Dane county Wisconsin. With over a decade of experience in strategic marketing and brand development for Fortune 300 companies, Andy blends business insight with a passion for fostering innovation and entrepreneurship. A lifelong learner and outdoor enthusiast, he’s deeply engaged in projects that strengthen Wisconsin’s creative and entrepreneurial ecosystems—helping founders, makers, and doers turn ideas into sustainable ventures.\n\nAndy is an avid disc golfer, pickleball fanatic, and die hard Packers fan. Andy lives in Sun Prairie, WI with his partner Sarah and son John.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/hector-gutierrez\n\n![Hector Gutierrez](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0i