{"chunk_id": "100state::69", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 69, "text": "Hector Gutierrez\n\nBio Coming Soon.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/abby-johnson\n\n![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDgwMCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n### Abby Johnson\n\nAbby Johnson is an artist and curator whose work centers on community, collaboration, and contemporary visual culture. She holds a BFA in Studio Art from The University of Texas at Austin, where she graduated with honors.\n\nShe is the co-founder and curator of R&D Madison, a neighborhood contemporary art gallery dedicated to presenting innovative exhibitions and supporting emerging and established artists. In addition to her curatorial practice, she works across the arts in event planning and operational support, contributing to the behind-the-scenes work that brings creative projects to life.\n\nHer artwork has been featured in exhibitions at the John Michael Kohler Arts Center in Sheboygan, WI; Arts + Literature Laboratory in Madison, WI; and the Visual Arts Center in Austin, TX. Her practice reflects a sustained commitment to building meaningful artistic networks and presenting work that engages thoughtfully with place and community.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/team_member/mushka\n\n![Mushka](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI5NjAiIGhlaWdodD0iOTYwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgOTYwIDk2MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)\n\n### Mushka\n\nArt Director\n\n##### “The creative adult is the child who survived.”\n\n— Ursula Le Guin", "char_len": 1664, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::70", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 70, "text": "Mushka\n\nArt Director\n\n##### “The creative adult is the child who survived.”\n\n— Ursula Le Guin\n\nMushka, the mastermind behind Madison’s Mushka Studios, is a vibrant virtuoso in the realms of art and performance. A graduate of The Museum School at Tufts, he orchestrates a symphony of skills, specializing in figurative painting, fanciful illustration, captivating costumes, and gorgeous graphic design. This creative conjurer has left his indelible mark on unique industries, enchanting clients like Warner Brothers, DC Comics, and Nickelodeon with his distinctive and dynamic styles, a dance between Classical and Contemporary techniques, nurtured by an ever-supportive circle of friends and family.\n\nBeyond his artistic exploits, Mushka passionately plucks the ethereal strings of the Theremin, weaving magical melodies that echo through the ethers. His heartfelt performances not only captivate audiences but also serve as a benevolent beacon, raising funds for children battling cancer.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/founders-circle-ignite-program-empowering-madison-entrepreneurs-with-100state\n\n# Founder’s Circle Ignite Program: Empowering Madison Entrepreneurs with 100state\n\n![100state & NHTI Founders Circle Gradutation](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxNDMyIiBoZWlnaHQ9Ijc0NiIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDE0MzIgNzQ2Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\nPosted on November 27, 2024\n\n![Founder's Circle Ignite](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjI1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDIyNSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)The entrepreneurial spirit is alive and thriving in Madison, Wisconsin, thanks to the Founder’s Circle Ignite program. This initiative, designed to foster innovation and support local entrepreneurs, recently celebrated its graduation ceremony, marking a significant milestone for the program and its participants.", "char_len": 2040, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::71", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 71, "text": "spirit is alive and thriving in Madison, Wisconsin, thanks to the Founder’s Circle Ignite program. This initiative, designed to foster innovation and support local entrepreneurs, recently celebrated its graduation ceremony, marking a significant milestone for the program and its participants.\n\nAt the heart of this success is **100state**, Madison’s premier coworking space, which plays a pivotal role in nurturing entrepreneurial talent and driving economic growth in the region.  This was also the first of many partnerships with NHTI, to increase entrepreneurship development in the Madison Community\n\n#### What is the Founder’s Circle Ignite Program?\n\nThe Founder’s Circle Ignite program is a dynamic initiative aimed at equipping aspiring entrepreneurs with the tools, resources, and mentorship they need to turn their ideas into thriving businesses. This innovative collaborative initiative between 100state and NHTI, transforms local entrepreneurs’ dreams into thriving businesses, strengthening Madison’s growing startup ecosystem.\n\nThe program focuses on fostering innovation, building community connections, and providing hands-on learning experiences. Participants gain access to workshops, networking opportunities, and expert guidance, all tailored to help them navigate the challenges of starting and scaling a business. This year’s cohort included a diverse group of entrepreneurs, each bringing unique ideas and perspectives to the table.  Among the graduates were individuals like **Adam Jun**, **Kiara Allen**, **James Gui**, and **Dr. Giselle Argento-Berrios**, who represent the next wave of innovative thinkers and business leaders in Madison.\n\n#### 100state: The Backbone of Madison’s Entrepreneurial Ecosystem\n\nAs Madison’s largest coworking community, **100state** has been instrumental in supporting the Founder’s Circle Ignite program. Located in the heart of the city, 100state provides a collaborative environment where entrepreneurs, freelancers, and creatives can thrive. Its mission is to empower individuals to create meaningful change through innovation and community engagement.\n\n**Key Contributions of 100state to the Founder’s Circle Ignite Program:**", "char_len": 2188, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
