{"chunk_id": "100state::93", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 93, "text": "Categories\n\n* 100arts (11)\n* 100stories (11)\n* AI (1)\n* Blockchain (1)\n* Community (30)\n* coworking (4)\n* entrepreneur (9)\n* Events (11)\n* Freelancers (8)\n* Member of the Month (23)\n* Membership (23)\n* Nonprofit (7)\n* Social Marketing (3)\n* Startups (16)\n* Uncategorized (79)\n* Working Remote (8)\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/3-reasons-why-i-love-coworking-as-a-digital-nomad-and-solopreneur\n\n# 3 Reasons Why I Love Coworking as a Digital Nomad and Solopreneur\n\n![community-support](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxNDAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwNTAiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCAxNDAwIDEwNTAiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=)\n\nPosted on March 21, 2024\n\n*The following blog post was written by long-time 100state member and solopreneur, Olivia Barrow.*\n\n![Solopreneur Olivia Borrow](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzAwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDMwMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)When I quit my job in 2016 to launch my SEO strategy and content creation business, I was excited to become a solopreneur digital nomad, meaning I could perform my job from anywhere. For the first nine months, I did just that. I bounced around between a dozen different coffee shops in Madison, my partner’s apartment, my parents’ house in North Carolina, and the Red River Gorge in Kentucky, until I decided to really embrace the digital nomad stereotype and bought a ticket to Bangkok. I spent nine weeks backpacking around South East Asia, fitting my work in between rock climbing days and sightseeing days.\n\nWhile I had a wonderful time in Thailand, Vietnam, and Cambodia and will never forget the experiences I had there, when I got home from the trip, I was desperately craving something that I’d had a hard time finding ever since I quit my job: community.\n\nBefore the jet lag even wore off, I started touring coworking spaces in Madison, looking not just for a quiet space to focus but a place where I would feel grounded in routine and community. I wanted a place to belong. After evaluating five or six different options around the city, I landed at 100state, and I’ve been here ever since.", "char_len": 2285, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::94", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 94, "text": "started touring coworking spaces in Madison, looking not just for a quiet space to focus but a place where I would feel grounded in routine and community. I wanted a place to belong. After evaluating five or six different options around the city, I landed at 100state, and I’ve been here ever since.\n\n100state stands out in the Madison coworking scene for several reasons. As one of the only nonprofit coworking spaces in the area, the rates are very affordable. Secondly, it’s an active art gallery, with a rotating selection of art from dozens of Madison-based artists hanging on the walls year round. It adds so much color to the space, and when I’m in need of inspiration, sometimes I gaze at one of my favorite paintings and let my mind wander. But in my opinion, the most important way 100state stands out is the community. The community at 100state is one of the most vibrant I’ve ever experienced in a coworking space (and I’ve been a member at two others during some other extended periods of travel). At 100state, the regulars know each other by name. Our lunch room is one of the first things you see off the elevator, which makes it a natural gathering place. We chat, share food and snacks, and recently, thanks to community manager Kelly Pagac, we’ve even been practicing yoga and mediation together.\n\nBut the community isn’t the only thing I love about 100state and about coworking in general. I’ve broken it down into three reasons I love coworking.\n\n**1. Networking with Other Business Owners**\n\nAs a solopreneur business owner, maintaining a membership at 100state has provided excellent networking opportunities, even when I wasn’t looking for them. I’m an extrovert, so I’m always making an effort to get to know other members, whether they are remote workers, artists, grad students, interns, or entrepreneurs like me. And throughout the years, these efforts have frequently turned into opportunities for my business. The affordable month-to-month membership fee attracts many entrepreneurs who are still in the early stages of their business, and through the years I’ve helped a few business owners create foundational content for their websites. I’ve also gotten excellent referrals to some long-term clients from connections I made over the lunch table at 100state.", "char_len": 2289, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::95", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 95, "text": "many entrepreneurs who are still in the early stages of their business, and through the years I’ve helped a few business owners create foundational content for their websites. I’ve also gotten excellent referrals to some long-term clients from connections I made over the lunch table at 100state.\n\n**2. Personal and Professional Development Opportunities**\n\n100state has always been a place for knowledge sharing. In the early years, it was known for hosting community-wide brainstorming and problem-solving sessions. Through the years the types of events have changed, but there have been dozens of free educational events, workshops, panels about topics ranging from how to get a business loan and other challenges entrepreneurs face to workshops about mindfulness, creativity, and personal finance. One cool knowledge-sharing opportunity that Kelly recently launched is what we’re calling “AV Club,” a support group and cheering squad for anybody who wants to dabble in short-form video marketing. Before the club launched, I hadn’t been seriously thinking about doing any video marketing for my business. But now, knowing I’ll have peers to bounce ideas off of, learn logistical tips and tricks from, and get feedback from, I’m excited to dive into a project that might just be transformative for my business.\n\n**3. A Home Base in Downtown Madison**\n\nI love that 100state is located in the heart of downtown Madison. I live a few miles east of downtown, so it takes me about 20 minutes to commute to the office. In the winter, I enjoy reading a book on my quiet commute on the bus, and when the weather warms up, I ride my bike for more flexibility (although, if I’m honest, I miss the built-in reading time on the bus!). But whether I’m biking or busing, the commute helps me mentally and emotionally separate my work life from my personal life.", "char_len": 1850, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::96", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 96, "text": "on my quiet commute on the bus, and when the weather warms up, I ride my bike for more flexibility (although, if I’m honest, I miss the built-in reading time on the bus!). But whether I’m biking or busing, the commute helps me mentally and emotionally separate my work life from my personal life.\n\nWe have a secure indoor bike garage on the first floor, which makes it really easy to bike in. And on days where big events are happening downtown, like Concerts on the Square, it’s a big perk to not fight for a bike parking spot (much less a car parking spot!). If I want to go for a bike ride on a nice evening after work, I feel comfortable leaving my stuff for a few hours in the office and using my 24/7 keycard to get back in later — so I can maximize the daylight hours instead of losing time commuting.\n\nIf you’re a soloentrepreneur craving community, routine, and a quiet place free from the distractions that can arise at home, check out a membership at 100state!\n\nPrevious Post\n\nKey Benefits of Consulting a Mentor for Your Business Idea\n\nNext Post\n\nWhy 100state is the Ultimate Startup Hub in Madison WI\n\n## Recent Posts\n\n* Founders Circle Ignite: The Ultimate Entrepreneurial Bootcamp at 100state\n  February 9, 2025\n* 100state: Madison’s Entrepreneurs hub to Ignite Dreams\n  February 9, 2025\n* Top 5 Benefits of Coworking for Startups in Madison\n  November 28, 2024\n* Founder’s Circle Ignite Program: Empowering Madison Entrepreneurs with 100state\n  November 27, 2024\n* The Benefits of Coworking for Mental Health and Productivity\n  November 23, 2024\n\n## Categories\n\n* 100arts (11)\n* 100stories (11)\n* AI (1)\n* Blockchain (1)\n* Community (30)\n* coworking (4)\n* entrepreneur (9)\n* Events (11)\n* Freelancers (8)\n* Member of the Month (23)\n* Membership (23)\n* Nonprofit (7)\n* Social Marketing (3)\n* Startups (16)\n* Uncategorized (79)\n* Working Remote (8)\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/10-key-benefits-of-consulting-a-mentor-for-your-business-idea\n\n# Key Benefits of Consulting a Mentor for Your Business Idea\n\n![entrepreneur-side-hustle](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMjAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjkwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDEyMDAgOTAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\nPosted on January 22, 2024", "char_len": 2295, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::97", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 97, "text": "for Your Business Idea\n\n![entrepreneur-side-hustle](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMjAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjkwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDEyMDAgOTAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\nPosted on January 22, 2024\n\nEmbarking on an entrepreneurial journey can be thrilling yet daunting. One crucial step often overlooked by many aspiring entrepreneurs is the invaluable role of a mentor. When you have a business idea, consulting with a mentor can be the difference between a successful launch and a missed opportunity. This article delves into the myriad benefits of mentorship in business and entrepreneurship.\n\nLet’s jump in!\n\n##### Understanding the Concept of Business Mentorship\n\nBusiness mentorship is an arrangement where an experienced professional provides guidance, knowledge, and advice to someone just starting or looking to grow in business. Unlike advisors or coaches, mentors offer more personalized and long-term support, focusing on overall development rather than just specific issues.\n\n##### The Importance of Mentorship in Early Business Stages\n\nIn the initial stages of a business, the path is fraught with challenges and unknowns. With their experience and expertise, a mentor can help navigate these rough waters, offering advice tailored to the unique challenges of startups.\n\n##### Mentorship and Business Strategy Development\n\nStrategizing is crucial in business, and a mentor can play a pivotal role in refining your business ideas. They bring a fresh perspective, often backed by their own successes and failures, to help you develop a robust business strategy.\n\n##### Networking Opportunities through Mentorship\n\nA significant advantage of having a mentor is access to their network. A well-connected mentor can open doors to partnerships, resources, and opportunities otherwise inaccessible to budding entrepreneurs.\n\n##### Learning from Experience: Gaining Insights from a Mentor’s Journey\n\nThe journey of a mentor is a goldmine of lessons and insights. By sharing their experiences, mentors provide a real-life context to business challenges, offering a more practical understanding than any textbook.\n\n##### Avoiding Common Pitfalls: How a Mentor Can Help", "char_len": 2274, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::98", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 98, "text": "from a Mentor’s Journey\n\nThe journey of a mentor is a goldmine of lessons and insights. By sharing their experiences, mentors provide a real-life context to business challenges, offering a more practical understanding than any textbook.\n\n##### Avoiding Common Pitfalls: How a Mentor Can Help\n\nBusiness is often a trial-and-error process, but a mentor can help in steering clear of common mistakes. Learning from their experiences can save you from costly missteps.\n\n##### Mentors as a Source of Motivation and Support\n\nStarting a business can be a lonely journey. A mentor can offer much-needed emotional support and motivation, especially during tough times, helping you stay focused and resilient.\n\n##### Customized Guidance: Tailoring Advice to Your Specific Business Idea\n\nEach business idea is unique, and so should be the advice you receive. A mentor provides tailored guidance, ensuring that the advice is relevant to your specific business model and industry.\n\n##### Critical Feedback and Its Importance\n\nConstructive criticism is vital for growth. Mentors provide honest feedback, helping you to develop resilience and learn from your weaknesses.\n\n##### Mentorship in Enhancing Leadership Skills\n\nEffective leadership is crucial for business success. Mentorship can play a significant role in honing your leadership skills, preparing you to manage teams and lead your business effectively.\n\n##### Financial Guidance and Resource Management\n\nFinancial mismanagement can quickly lead to business failure. A mentor with expertise in finance can guide you in resource allocation, budgeting, and financial planning.\n\n##### Innovating and Pivoting with Mentor Input\n\nThe ability to innovate and pivot is essential in today’s fast-paced business world. A mentor can provide critical insights and guidance in adapting and evolving your business model to stay competitive.\n\n##### Building a Strong Business Foundation with Mentorship\n\nA mentor helps lay a solid foundation for your business, emphasizing sustainability and long-term success over quick, short-term gains.\n\n##### Global Perspectives: Learning from a Mentor with Diverse Experience\n\nA mentor with a diverse background can provide a broader perspective, helping you think globally and expanding the scope of your business idea.", "char_len": 2290, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::99", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 99, "text": "emphasizing sustainability and long-term success over quick, short-term gains.\n\n##### Global Perspectives: Learning from a Mentor with Diverse Experience\n\nA mentor with a diverse background can provide a broader perspective, helping you think globally and expanding the scope of your business idea.\n\n##### Mentorship and Personal Growth\n\nMentorship is not just about business growth but personal development, too. It helps balance personal and professional life, leading to overall growth and fulfillment.\n\n##### How to Find and Choose the Right Mentor for Your Business Idea\n\nSelecting the right mentor is critical. Look for someone with relevant experience, a network beneficial to your field, and a mentoring style that matches your learning preferences.\n\n---\n\nThe benefits of consulting a mentor when you have a business idea are manifold. From strategic insights to emotional support, a mentor can guide you through the complexities of entrepreneurship, setting you on the path to success.\n\nAt 100state, we understand how crucial this mentorship is in the entrepreneurial journey. That’s why we’ve joined forces with MERLIN Mentors, allowing you to tap into this invaluable resource.\n\nWe’re excited to offer regular office hours every 2nd Tuesday of the month.\n\nThis collaboration is more than just a meeting; it’s a bridge connecting you to the wisdom and experience of seasoned professionals, ready to guide you as you navigate the exciting yet challenging world of developing your next business idea!\n\nJoin us in harnessing the power of mentorship to turn your aspirations into achievements.\n\nCheck out our events page to find out the next date and link to register!\n\nPrevious Post\n\nThe Spark of Shared Ambition: Why Community Ignites Success at 100state Coworking\n\nNext Post\n\n3 Reasons Why I Love Coworking as a Digital Nomad and Solopreneur\n\n## Recent Posts\n\n* Founders Circle Ignite: The Ultimate Entrepreneurial Bootcamp at 100state\n  February 9, 2025\n* 100state: Madison’s Entrepreneurs hub to Ignite Dreams\n  February 9, 2025\n* Top 5 Benefits of Coworking for Startups in Madison\n  November 28, 2024\n* Founder’s Circle Ignite Program: Empowering Madison Entrepreneurs with 100state\n  November 27, 2024\n* The Benefits of Coworking for Mental Health and Productivity\n  November 23, 2024", "char_len": 2298, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::100", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 100, "text": "hub to Ignite Dreams\n  February 9, 2025\n* Top 5 Benefits of Coworking for Startups in Madison\n  November 28, 2024\n* Founder’s Circle Ignite Program: Empowering Madison Entrepreneurs with 100state\n  November 27, 2024\n* The Benefits of Coworking for Mental Health and Productivity\n  November 23, 2024\n\n## Categories\n\n* 100arts (11)\n* 100stories (11)\n* AI (1)\n* Blockchain (1)\n* Community (30)\n* coworking (4)\n* entrepreneur (9)\n* Events (11)\n* Freelancers (8)\n* Member of the Month (23)\n* Membership (23)\n* Nonprofit (7)\n* Social Marketing (3)\n* Startups (16)\n* Uncategorized (79)\n* Working Remote (8)\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/adam-villegas\n\n![Adam Villegas](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMDAiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCAxMDAwIDEwMDAiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=)\n\n## Adam Villegas\n\nhttps://livingoutunrealdreams.com\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/livingoutunrealdreams/\n\nAdam Villegas is a Milwaukee native, Madison based artist and curator. After earning a Bachelor of Fine Arts degree from UW-Madison in 2014, Villegas continued to pursue his passion for painting, serigraphy, and creating environments for artists to thrive. Upon graduating he established Living Out Unreal Dreams (LOUD) clothing company where he designs and prints his own wearable artwork and hosts events consisting of a blend of artistic, fashion and musical expression. The sounds and lyricism of HipHop is one of his main influences as well as his cultural background, family, friends, and social experiences. He has taught workshops based on art, graffiti, printing and muralism in programs through The Bubbler, Arts & Literature Lab, Briarpatch and other local organizations.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/adrew-christensen\n\n![Andrew Christensen](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MTQiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDcxNCAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n## Adrew Christensen\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/andrew.christensen.7967\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/christensenandrew/", "char_len": 2201, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::101", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 101, "text": "Adrew Christensen\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/andrew.christensen.7967\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/christensenandrew/\n\nAndrew Christensen is an artist and musician searching for lost treasure in the forgotten sands of time. Fascinated by cultural artifacts of the 1920’s-60’s, he is always on the hunt for another piece of obscure expression – scratchy Blind Lemon Jefferson records, the 1927 film Metropolis, the children’s book illustrations of Dorothy P. Lathrop and the Dada photomontages of Hannah Höch have a certain ghostly magnetism and haunting beauty that informs his style. Due to a rare eye condition called Achromatopsia, he is legally blind, sees only in black and white and has extreme light sensitivity. His art is a means to communicate how he sees and highlight the absurd silliness of our tragic society.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/alejandro-punbra\n\n![Alejandro Punbra](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMDAiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCAxMDAwIDEwMDAiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=)\n\n## Alejandro Punbra\n\nMeet Nilvio Alexander Punguil Bravo, an artist greeting from Ecuador who has been infusing his artwork with the vibrant colors of Latin culture since he was a young child. Despite being self-taught, he skillfully exerts each brush stroke and color on his palette to create stunning pieces inspired by his observations of the world around him.\n\nWhen he moved to the United States, he faced the challenge of adapting to a new culture without knowing English. However, his art proved to be a powerful tool for communication. Not only did it allow him to express himself, but it also helped him find his place in Madison, Wisconsin.", "char_len": 1772, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::102", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 102, "text": "around him.\n\nWhen he moved to the United States, he faced the challenge of adapting to a new culture without knowing English. However, his art proved to be a powerful tool for communication. Not only did it allow him to express himself, but it also helped him find his place in Madison, Wisconsin.\n\nSince 2010, Alex has been making waves in the Madison art scene with his exhibitions and fundraisers. Even while attending the University of Wisconsin-Madison, he continues to pursue his passion for art in his free time. His canvases are more than just paintings – they represent a blend of emotions, cultural influences, social justice, and personal identity. His art serves as a bridge that brings people from different backgrounds together, transcending language and racial barriers.\n\nAt this event, get ready to experience the essence of “Fuego y Forma” through Alex’s creations. His artwork embodies the intricate forms and fiery passion that define his Latin roots. And do not be surprised if he expresses himself through music on the drums and guitar or his poetic words – art knows no limits for Alex.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/amy-m-weh\n\n![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMDAiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCAxMDAwIDEwMDAiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=)\n\n## Amy M. Weh\n\nhttps://www.mosaicweh.com\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/mosaicweh\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/mosaicweh/\n\nFor as far back as I can remember, I have always wanted to be an artist. I was brought up in a very creative family that believed and nurtured the idea that you need to do what truly makes you happy. I have continued to produce mosaics in many forms for the last twenty-five plus years, developing new techniques and methods along the way. All of these experiences have collectively brought me to a self-realization that mosaic art is my found medium.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/amy-regutti\n\n![Amy Regutti](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3NjgiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDc2OCAxMDI0Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n## Amy Regutti\n\nhttps://www.amyreguttiart.com/", "char_len": 2292, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::103", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 103, "text": "Regutti](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3NjgiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDc2OCAxMDI0Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n## Amy Regutti\n\nhttps://www.amyreguttiart.com/\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/amyreguttiart/\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/spacethrob/\n\nAmy Regutti is a painter. Her paintings explore artificial intelligence, body adornment, characters that lurk in the forest and both the beauty and loss of nature as we know it. Amy exhibits locally and nationally. Her paintings have shown in Surreal Salon 11, 12 and 14 at the Baton Rouge Gallery.\n\nAmy graduated with a BFA from Northern Illinois University and a MSOM from the Midwest College of Oriental Medicine. She lives and works in Madison Wisconsin with her husband Roger.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/andre-ferrella\n\n![Andre Ferrella](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzODAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDQ2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzgwIDQ0NiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)\n\n## Andre Ferrella\n\nhttp://andreartist.com/\n\nAndre Ferrella graduated as a Medical Illustrator from the University of Toledo/Toledo Museum of Art School of Design and received a Master of Fine Arts degree from the University of Wisconsin-Madison.\n\nHe discovered an organic photographic process called “The Living Pictures”, also know as “The Mold Picture Process”, that bridged the gap between micro and macro space. He has been nationally and internationally collected and exhibited at renowned institutions.\n\nKnown as “The Artist of The Spirit” who devotes his life to bring Divine information from the other side of the veil. During a reading from Lee Carroll, KRYON described Andre as “The Evolutionary Artist, a Master of Light”. Andre brings the gift of accessing the other side of the veil via interdimensional devices he has created.", "char_len": 1975, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::104", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 104, "text": "who devotes his life to bring Divine information from the other side of the veil. During a reading from Lee Carroll, KRYON described Andre as “The Evolutionary Artist, a Master of Light”. Andre brings the gift of accessing the other side of the veil via interdimensional devices he has created.\n\nAndre brings to his art a lifetime of spiritual study and exploration of the world’s sacred traditions and iconography. With his indisputable technical virtuosity, Ferrella is able to reveal higher orders of reality and the interconnectedness of existence that has been described by ageless enlightened teachers and mystics. Ferrella communicates these ineffable spiritual experiences and phenomena, at the same time that he enables our own explorations and awakenings.\n\nAndre Ferrella taught Creative Fine Art, Photography and Visual Design at the University of Wisconsin-Whitewater.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/angelica-contreras\n\n![Angelica Contreras](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NjciIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwMCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDY2NyAxMDAwIj48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBmaWxsPSIjY2ZkNGRiIi8+PC9zdmc+)\n\n## Angelica Contreras\n\nhttps://www.angelicacontreras.net/\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/senoritagalleta/\n\nAngelica Contreras is a Latinx artist who explores the multi-layered relationships between identity, tradition, and popular culture. Growing up in the US and Mexico provided a rich palette of imagery for Contreras. Within her artwork, there is an element of nostalgia present in its layers; sometimes reminiscent of childhood, adolescence or tying in specific cultural references and traditions. Contreras incorporates the mediums of acrylic and oil painting and techniques of collage into her artwork, creating a rich palette of colors and textures. Her use of materials is as calculated as it is serendipitous, resulting in unusual cultural combinations and visual compositions. Her work acts as a bridge between various communities and cultures while reflecting her own life experiences.", "char_len": 2077, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::105", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 105, "text": "artwork, creating a rich palette of colors and textures. Her use of materials is as calculated as it is serendipitous, resulting in unusual cultural combinations and visual compositions. Her work acts as a bridge between various communities and cultures while reflecting her own life experiences.\n\nContreras was born in Whittier, California and moved to Guadalajara, Jalisco at an early age. She attended the University of Guadalajara, receiving a B.A. in art in 2008 and a Masters in Art Education in 2016. Her artwork has been shown in exhibitions in Mexico and the U.S., including “Caja de Visiones” at Madison Museum of Contemporary Art and “The Hidden Faces/ Los Rostros Ocultos” at Latino Arts Inc in Milwaukee. Contreras was a recipient of the Forward Art Prize in 2020, an annual award targeted to support the work of female artists in Dane County. She currently lives and works in Madison, Wisconsin, where she continues to create and showcase her art.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/ann-haberl\n\n![Ann Haberl](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MjAiIGhlaWdodD0iOTYwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzIwIDk2MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)\n\n## Ann Haberl\n\nhttps://annhaberl.com\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/meditativelandscapes/", "char_len": 1334, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::106", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 106, "text": "Ann Haberl\n\nhttps://annhaberl.com\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/meditativelandscapes/\n\nThere is a stillness in my work. It’s the way you feel when time seems to stop – at birth, death, and if you’re lucky during some awestruck moment in your life. Paradoxically, it is also the way you feel when time is racing by – clouds casting complex shadows on a lake, the changing sky at dusk. I’m holding that note in my paintings. The content of my work is about the transitory nature of images, indeed of life. The light is moving, and in a breath it will be gone. I paint to catch that moment, the moment before the light goes. As in meditation, there is no clear destination here. You will not end up at the little red barn. There is mystery and permission to wander. The narrative, if any, is ethereal. A subtle supernatural quality touches all of my work. There is a presence and a vastness. I don’t dictate the presence, I just invite it. The invitation sometimes starts with a respectful disregard for the classic tradition of atmospheric perspective. The juxtaposition of a loose painterly foreground – often pushed to abstraction – and a tighter, focused background or middle ground contribute to a slightly off kilter feeling. The viewer is just a little uncomfortable in this soothing space, and being out of the comfort zone forces one to pay attention. Like a mental float tank the experience is one of relaxed alertness. In that dichotomy – the beautiful and the edgy – is the presence I beckon.\n\n## [page] https://100state.com/artists/annemarie-adams\n\n![Annemarie Adams](data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxMDAwIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMDAiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCAxMDAwIDEwMDAiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=)\n\n## Annemarie Adams\n\nhttps://www.annemarieadamsgallery.com\n\nTo me the physical world is a veil that falls in front of the energetic world. And the energetic world plays with us constantly. I love to watch and listen for the signs it sends us.", "char_len": 2041, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "100state::107", "doc_slug": "100state", "chunk_index": 107, "text": "Annemarie Adams\n\nhttps://www.annemarieadamsgallery.com\n\nTo me the physical world is a veil that falls in front of the energetic world. And the energetic world plays with us constantly. I love to watch and listen for the signs it sends us.\n\nWhen I take photographs I look for an essence that can be brought forward: a set of colors, a pattern, a texture, a contrast. I see that essence as a piece of art that can be made out of the composition of the photo. Sometimes the details are essential and at other times a distraction. I use different artistic styles to bring out the essence I see.\n\nI’ve had a lifelong love of photography that includes professional work directing commercial photo shoots.\n\nGiving back\n\nIt’s been a dream of mine to support music educators.\n\nMy Italian ancestors were classically trained musicians. I started learning Spanish classical guitar at age 8 and in high school, band was my refuge. In mid-life, I took classical voice lessons and was later accepted into the Madison Symphony Chorus, where I’ve been singing since 2014.\n\nI wear another hat in the music world, as host of a morning radio show. On-air I’m Ava Borelli, host of Ava Borelli’s Classical Jukebox on WORT 89.9 FM (wortfm.org) our local volunteer-powered community radio station. Together with my co-host Walter, we are on WORT FM each week combining classcial pops, film scores and mashups with banter, musician interviews, entertainment news and music history. None of this would have been possible without my music teachers.\n\nTo pay it forward, a portion of proceeds go to the Madison Youth Choir and the Save the Music Foundation.\n\nMy sense of affinity for The Big Easy runs deep, so a portion of the proceeds from the sale of New Orleans art goes to Youth Rebuilding New Orleans.\n\nThank you for supporting my small business and being part of this journey to bring music and purpose into the lives of many.", "char_len": 1904, "id": 20, "source": "100state", "type": "static_html", "category": "community", "url": "https://100state.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-future-founders::0", "doc_slug": "badger-future-founders", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "## [page] https://www.badgerfuturefounders.com\n\n# Empowering Future Entrepreneurs\n\nJoin Badger Future Founders and connect with fellow UW-Madison students passionate about innovation, entrepreneurship, and building the next big thing.\n\nJoin Our CommunityLearn More\n\nScroll for more\n\n## Join Badger Future Founders\n\nApplications are open for Spring 2026! Curious about startups, business, or just hearing real stories from founders? Join us any Wednesday to check it out! No commitment or experience required!\n\n### What We're About\n\n🎤\n\n#### Wednesday Speaker Nights\n\nHear from founders, CEOs, operators and then stick around for Q&A and conversation.\n\n🤝\n\n#### Low-Pressure, High-Value\n\nNo applications, no auditions. Just show up, listen, ask questions, and meet people.\n\n🌆\n\n#### More Than Just Talks\n\nNetworking events, pitch competitions, and trips to startup hubs like Chicago.\n\n🎓\n\n#### Built for Students\n\nAll majors welcome. Whether you're curious, building, or just exploring.\n\n### Join the Community", "char_len": 1005, "id": 14, "source": "Badger Future Founders", "type": "static_html", "category": "student-org", "url": "https://www.badgerfuturefounders.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::0", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "## [page] https://www.badgervc.com\n\n# Where Badgers Meet Venture Capital\n\nBadgerVC is a student led organization at UW-Madison dedicated to making venture capital accessible to undergraduates. Through speaker events, workshops, and discussions, we help students learn how investors evaluate startups and how venture capital shapes innovation.\n\nLearn more\n\n![The Capitol building in Washington, D.C. with a large dome topped with a golden statue, set against a clear blue sky.](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/0f56ef26-5082-42b0-9cf1-54d995bf3365/madison+capital+building.jpg)\n\n## Our Story\n\nBadgerVC was created to give UW-Madison undergraduates a space to explore venture capital.\n\nOriginally part of StratoVC, a group that has since transitioned into a student-managed venture fund, we launched BadgerVC as a dedicated student organization focused on education, community, and exposure to the VC world.\n\nOur goal is to make an often-exclusive industry approachable, inspiring students who are curious about startups, investing, or entrepreneurship.\n\n## Our Mission\n\nOur mission is to create accessible, real-world venture capital learning opportunities that empower undergraduates to explore, evaluate, and engage with early-stage investing.\n\nWe hope to provide meaningful learning experiences that make VC approachable and exciting!\n\nOur team is comprised of driven students pursuing various careers in and outside of the startup economy. We encourage all members interested in entrepreneurship, venture capital, and exploring early-stage startups or investing to join us!\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/043057f6-35c5-4e65-954a-49c73d54b27d/IMG_1152+%281%29.JPG)\n\n# Semester Calendar\n\n#### Meetings on Thursdays from 6-7pm\n\nCheck Calendar for Specific Dates and Times! Click through past months to catch up on past events!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/about", "char_len": 1951, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::1", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 1, "text": "Semester Calendar\n\n#### Meetings on Thursdays from 6-7pm\n\nCheck Calendar for Specific Dates and Times! Click through past months to catch up on past events!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/about\n\nBadgerVC is a student-run organization affiliated with the University of Wisconsin-Madison that aims to educate students about the fundamentals of venture capital and connect them to the broader Madison VC ecosystem.\n\n# What Is BadgerVC?\n\n# Opportunities\n\nWe provide opportunities for students of all backgrounds and experience levels to explore the world of early-stage investing through…\n\n* #### Speaker Events & Panels\n\n* #### Networking Events\n* #### Professional Development Opportunities\n\n![The Wisconsin School of Business building on a sunny day with a tree in the foreground and a few pedestrians walking outside.](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/83d10346-b8c9-4727-a8d4-470c4bc11e01/grainger+exterior.jpg)\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events\n\n#### **View upcoming events here!** Check out what we have planned next:\n\n---\n\n![End of Sem Social!](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1775673036439-R0XPL3L2YON82C0A6NDF/Screenshot+2026-04-08+at+1.30.18%E2%80%AFPM.png)\n\nApr\n\n23\n\n# End of Sem Social!\n\n* Thursday, April 23, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nMark your calendar for BadgerVC’s end of sem social!!\n\nMore details to come!\n\nView Event →\n\nApr\n\n16\n\n# Investment Memo Workshop\n\n* Thursday, April 16, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nInvestment memos are a key tool that venture capital firms use to evaluate startups and communicate investment decisions.\n\nIn this workshop, BadgerVC will guide you through the structure of a strong memo and show you how to write effective one-pagers.\n\nWhether you’re preparing for interviews or case competitions, this session will help you build a structured approach to analyzing startups and communicating persuasive recommendations.\n\nThis is a valuable skill for developing your perspective on different industries and emerging startups!\n\nView Event →\n\nApr\n\n9\n\n# BadgerVC Career Trek!\n\n* Thursday, April 9, 2026\n* 8:00 AM", "char_len": 2182, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::2", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 2, "text": "will help you build a structured approach to analyzing startups and communicating persuasive recommendations.\n\nThis is a valuable skill for developing your perspective on different industries and emerging startups!\n\nView Event →\n\nApr\n\n9\n\n# BadgerVC Career Trek!\n\n* Thursday, April 9, 2026\n* 8:00 AM\n\n6:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nBadgerVC members will head to Chicago to explore careers in venture capital, visiting 3–4 firms across the city!\n\nMembers will\n\n* hear directly from investors and operators about their career paths\n* build connections,\n* and get a behind-the-scenes look at how early-stage companies are evaluated and supported\n\nThis is a great opportunity to better understand the VC ecosystem, ask questions in a small-group setting, and gain insight into full-time career paths in startups and investing!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us &amp; What's Next](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774325839790-3Y5EID0QRMFWLE4IN35U/1773274915125.jpeg)\n\nMar\n\n12\n\n# Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next\n\n* Thursday, March 12, 2026\n* 5:30 PM\n\n6:30 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n2025 reshaped how founders build and how investors deploy, and the lessons are still unfolding.\n\nBadgerVC and Badger Future Founders (BFF) are teaming up to bring you two people with front-row seats:\n**Grant Watkin****s** — from Gener8tor, working directly with early-stage founders navigating launches, traction, and the real grind of building\n**Mason Co****ok** — founder of Mastercraft Ventures, who completed fundraising in early 2025 and is actively shaping what smart early-stage investing looks like right now\n\nDuring the event, we’ll discuss:\n• What separated startups that gained traction from those that stalled.\n• What investors are looking for at pre-seed and seed today.\n• How AI is changing the cost and speed of building.\n• What the fundraising environment looks like as we enter 2026.\n\nRSVP here! **https://lnkd.in/ggXruqMW**\n\nView Event →\n\n![BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326931480-RHBLW2F30NY4YB74VCS0/IMG_2122.jpg)\n\nMar\n\n5\n\n# BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio\n\n* Thursday, March 5, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS", "char_len": 2288, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::3", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 3, "text": "Event →\n\n![BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326931480-RHBLW2F30NY4YB74VCS0/IMG_2122.jpg)\n\nMar\n\n5\n\n# BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio\n\n* Thursday, March 5, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin BadgerVC for a hands-on session with a representative from the Wisconsin School of Business Career Engagement Studio!\n\nLearn how to craft a standout resume, refine your cover letter, and strengthen your communication skills to stand out in competitive recruiting processes. Bring a physical or digital copy of your resume for live reviews!\n\nSee you there!\n\nView Event →\n\n![VC Networking Event (StratoVC)](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1771530197872-PP58AKN2R6DS2P7CEO45/strato_networking_event.jpeg)\n\nFeb\n\n27\n\n# VC Networking Event (StratoVC)\n\n* Friday, February 27, 2026\n* 3:30 PM\n\n5:30 PM\n* Tech Exploration Lab\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n🚀 Join Strato VC’s first-ever venture capital networking event! We’re partnering with some of Madison’s leading VC & entrepreneurship student organizations, including **BadgerVC**, **UW Tec****h Exploration Lab**, **Transcend UW**, and **Women** **in Entrepreneurship - UW**, to bring valuable connections to innovation-minded students.\n\n🔗 RSVP now: **https://luma.com/fxixeluz**\n\n🤝 Student attendees will have the opportunity to connect with leading professionals in Wisconsin, with backgrounds in venture capital, VC law, entrepreneurship, and more!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Students in VC Panel ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1771530012651-C9KUH3LAC3IYH15MH9O8/Students+in+VC+-+title+page+%281%29.jpg)\n\nFeb\n\n26\n\n# Students in VC Panel\n\n* Thursday, February 26, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for our Students in VC Panel, where UW students with venture capital internship experience share their firsthand insights.\n\nPanelists will discuss:\n\n* How they landed their VC internships\n* What the recruiting & interviewing process looked like\n* What their day-to-day work involved\n* And what skills mattered most!\n\nView Event →", "char_len": 2161, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::4", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 4, "text": "where UW students with venture capital internship experience share their firsthand insights.\n\nPanelists will discuss:\n\n* How they landed their VC internships\n* What the recruiting & interviewing process looked like\n* What their day-to-day work involved\n* And what skills mattered most!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Member Kickoff 🎉](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769208954135-9A39B4VR93BX0BD6PGAN/Screen+Shot+2026-01-23+at+4.55.43+PM.png)\n\nFeb\n\n19\n\n# Member Kickoff 🎉\n\n* Thursday, February 19, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Room # will be released to members\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nAll accepted members, join us for our first official meeting!\n\nGet to know your fellow members and dive into what’s coming this semester.\n\nView Event →\n\n![Application Acceptances Released](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769208116111-MALA1W0GS0BA3DGGJV7A/Screen+Shot+2026-01-23+at+4.40.48+PM.png)\n\nFeb\n\n16\n\n# Application Acceptances Released\n\n* Monday, February 16, 2026\n* 7:00 PM\n\n8:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nOn the evening of Monday, February 16th, BadgerVC Application results will be emailed out to members.\n\nView Event →\n\n![Applications Close](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769196270343-342K5T0EC85PNHWUT2EZ/Screen+Shot+2026-01-23+at+1.24.15+PM.png)\n\nFeb\n\n11\n\n# Applications Close\n\n* Wednesday, February 11, 2026\n* 11:58 PM\n\n11:59 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nApplications for Spring Membership close on Wednesday, February 11th at 11:59PM.\n\nApplications must be submitted on time to be considered.\n\nView Event →\n\n![Spring Organization Fair](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769195986170-76OXUX5GVD3BB8MSZGLE/huffman-keel-partners-kohl-center.webp)\n\nFeb\n\n10\n\n# Spring Organization Fair\n\n* Tuesday, February 10, 2026\n* 5:00 PM\n\n8:00 PM\n* Kohl Center\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nSwing by the BadgerVC table at the Spring Org Fair! Meet our team, hear what we’re working on this semester, and learn how you can get involved.\n\nWe’re excited to meet you!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Info Meeting](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769195730973-TM7J3QA6C71YYVENEPH0/WSB_GraingerExt_Spring_0515_007-e1572620705562.jpg)\n\nFeb\n\n5", "char_len": 2295, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::5", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 5, "text": "what we’re working on this semester, and learn how you can get involved.\n\nWe’re excited to meet you!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Info Meeting](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769195730973-TM7J3QA6C71YYVENEPH0/WSB_GraingerExt_Spring_0515_007-e1572620705562.jpg)\n\nFeb\n\n5\n\n# Info Meeting\n\n* Thursday, February 5, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Grainger Hall - Room 1180\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nLearn what BadgerVC is all about! We’ll share our mission, how to get involved, and the events we are planning for the semester.\n\nCome chat, ask questions, and connect with fellow students!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Applications are Open](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769196682139-ION7NLKGGZT66YFZC4NP/Screen+Shot+2026-01-23+at+1.31.00+PM.png)\n\nJan\n\n30\n\n# Applications are Open\n\n* Friday, January 30, 2026\n* 8:00 AM\n\n8:01 AM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nApplications for BadgerVC Spring Membership will open on the evening of Thursday, January 29th.\n\nApplications will close on February 11th.\n\nPlease reach out to badgervc@gmail.com with any questions regarding applications!\n\nView Event →\n\n![BBA Organization Fair](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769193836333-M7BDOPJP9E33D90I85LG/2015-11-04-gordon-dusk-exterior-fall-1-600x400.jpeg)\n\nJan\n\n29\n\n# BBA Organization Fair\n\n* Thursday, January 29, 2026\n* 4:00 PM\n\n6:00 PM\n* Gordon Commons\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us at the BBA Org Fair on Thursday, January 29th to learn more about WSB student orgs!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Qdoba Fundraiser](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1769194249800-OAIXNP2P5TCCF8X93HUD/BadgerVC+Qdoba+Fundraiser+Design.png)\n\nJan\n\n26\n\n# Qdoba Fundraiser\n\n* Monday, January 26, 2026\n* 4:00 PM\n\n8:00 PM\n* Qdoba\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nGrab a bite to eat & support BadgerVC! Swing by the State street Qdoba between 4-8PM on Monday, January 26th.\n\nYou can order online and enter the digital coupon code **QDOBAGIVES** or show the BadgerVC Qdoba Flyer in store. BadgerVC will receive 25% of sales - we appreciate your support!\n\n*You can also find this flyer on our Instagram page @badgervc\\_ for your convenience.*\n\nView Event →", "char_len": 2236, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::6", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 6, "text": "January 26th.\n\nYou can order online and enter the digital coupon code **QDOBAGIVES** or show the BadgerVC Qdoba Flyer in store. BadgerVC will receive 25% of sales - we appreciate your support!\n\n*You can also find this flyer on our Instagram page @badgervc\\_ for your convenience.*\n\nView Event →\n\n![Inside a Venture-Backed Startup: A Recruiting & Networking Event with Traba](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774325374341-BD40LQCK39CKOE2TOM6Z/traba.jpeg)\n\nOct\n\n24\n\n# Inside a Venture-Backed Startup: A Recruiting & Networking Event with Traba\n\n* Friday, October 24, 2025\n* 5:00 PM\n\n6:00 PM\n* Discovery to Product Building\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nThis Friday, October 24th at 5:00 PM, **BadgerVC** and **Transcend UW** will be hosting an exclusive session at 1403 University Avenue. All majors (and interested UW students are welcome!)\n\n**Traba** is a fast-growing startup backed by over $45M in funding from leading investors including Khosla Ventures, Founders Fund, and General Catalyst. Traba is a workforce management platform that connects businesses with vetted hourly workers, helping companies fill shifts efficiently.\n\nWe’ll hear directly from **Noah Thurer** (Growth Operations @ Traba) about what it’s like to work at a high-growth startup, navigate rapid expansion, and build a career in a fast-paced, venture-backed environment.\n\nView Event →\n\nOct\n\n24\n\n# Fall Social!\n\n* Friday, October 24, 2025\n* 2:00 PM\n\n3:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nTake a break and join **BadgerVC** for our Fall Social - come enjoy some cookies and chat with other BadgerVC members + exec members!\n\nCasual & and open to all BadgerVC members!\n\nLocation is in Flare!\n\nView Event →\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326432550-6QK0PXRK6I541EV5NHF6/IMG_2120.jpg)\n\nOct\n\n23\n\nVC 101\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\n* Thursday, October 23, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an in-depth session with Richelle Martin as we break down the key mechanics behind venture capital deals and fund operations.", "char_len": 2216, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::7", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 7, "text": "3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\n* Thursday, October 23, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an in-depth session with Richelle Martin as we break down the key mechanics behind venture capital deals and fund operations.\n\nWe'll explore term sheet basics (the key elements of an investment agreement), portfolio strategy, the roles of different investors when structuring deals, and fund governance.\n\nThis is a great session to learn about the building blocks of a venture capital deal, and grow your understanding of VC fund operations. See you there!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Team Leads Due Diligence Workshop ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1760986904416-QS0WTTYPVYJ22IPBMLSQ/Screen+Shot+2025-10-20+at+2.01.33+PM.png)\n\nOct\n\n21\n\n# Team Leads Due Diligence Workshop\n\n* Tuesday, October 21, 2025\n* 7:00 PM\n\n8:00 PM\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n**Session 1: 10/21**\n\n**Session 2: 10/28**\n\nDuring this session, you'll be introduced to a real startup and guided through the process of conducting due diligence.\n\nOur team leads will first walk members through a Due Diligence presentation, and then members will be paired up and assigned a specific area of the company to analyze, with plenty of support from our team leads if needed.\n\nThis is a low-pressure, learning focused environment! Team leads will be available throughout to provide guidance and answer questions.\n\nYou’ll also have time to complete your due diligence section asynchronously, before meeting again the following Tuesday.\n\nQuestions? Shoot us a message in Flare!\n\nView Event →\n\n![How to Think Like an Investor ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1757262343994-6367EIVS62XR5N14XPJR/1100-W.png)\n\nOct\n\n16\n\n# How to Think Like an Investor\n\n* Thursday, October 16, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:30 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS", "char_len": 1970, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::8", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 8, "text": "Investor ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1757262343994-6367EIVS62XR5N14XPJR/1100-W.png)\n\nOct\n\n16\n\n# How to Think Like an Investor\n\n* Thursday, October 16, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:30 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nHow to Think Like an Investor\n**Featuring: Angel Padulo, Founder, Angel Investor, and Chief Operating Officer at Treasure Coast Ventures**\nDiscover what truly resonates with investors in Angel Padulo’s session on thinking like an investor - especially when presenting to VCs. Understanding what matters most to investors is essential for any founder looking to secure funding.\n\nWalk away knowing what to look for as a future investor!\n\nView Event →\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326450303-KKPW91UTFU2HVLNLIDRC/IMG_2119.jpg)\n\nOct\n\n9\n\nVC 101\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\n* Thursday, October 9, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an engaging session with Christian Kaczmarczyk, Principal at Third Prime, as he shares how VCs discover and assess promising startups.\n\nDeal Sourcing: How investors identify opportunities through networks, accelerators, and outreach.\n\nDue Diligence: The process of digging deeper into a startup’s market, financials, team, and product to decide if it’s worth investing in.\n\nThis session offers a practical inside look at the VC decision process, and a first hand look at Third Prime's process. See you there!\n\nView Event →\n\n![VC Q&amp;A w/ Liam Krut, Investment Partner at Reinforced Ventures](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326527889-Z6K0I3FIXOTSD4KR0AJ4/4580-w-1-600x400-1.png)\n\nOct\n\n2\n\n# VC Q&A w/ Liam Krut, Investment Partner at Reinforced Ventures\n\n* Thursday, October 2, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nCurious about what it’s really like to work in VC? Join us for an open virtual Q&A with Liam Krut, Investment Partner at Reinforced Ventures, a firm investing at the frontier of robotics, biotech, and engineering.", "char_len": 2248, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::9", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 9, "text": "BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nCurious about what it’s really like to work in VC? Join us for an open virtual Q&A with Liam Krut, Investment Partner at Reinforced Ventures, a firm investing at the frontier of robotics, biotech, and engineering.\n\nThis is a great opportunity to hear first-hand insights and words of advice, and ask any burning questions!\n\nWe’re excited to see you there! Note that Liam is joining us virtually, but we are still meeting in person for this event.\n\nView Event →\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics &amp; Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326471867-4W99IPC59D7ZZ56JEQ0X/IMG_2118.jpg)\n\nSep\n\n25\n\nVC 101\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics & Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\n* Thursday, September 25, 2025\n* 6:30 PM\n\n7:30 PM\n* Grainger Hall, Room 1175\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for **VC 101: Intro to VC Basics + Recruiting**with Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\nThursday, Sept 25 | 6:30 - 7:30 PM at Grainger Hall Room 1175\n\nHear from Jonathon Horne, Managing Director of Idea Fund, and Sri Manikandan, UW student and current Idea Fund intern.\n\n* Learn the basics of venture capital\n* What investors look for\n* What founders should know about raising funding\n* And VC myths!\n\nPlus, get an inside look at Idea Fund, network with fellow students, **and explore opportunities to work with startups and VCs!**This session is open to **ALL students** - no experience required. RSVP **here** (resume upload is optional).\n\n\\*\\*Future events will be for BadgerVC Members only\n\nView Event →\n\n![BadgerVC Info Meeting](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1756868492662-XW7ONJEVW5RMERWBHTTK/grainger+lecture+hall.png)\n\nSep\n\n18\n\n# BadgerVC Info Meeting\n\n* Thursday, September 18, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Grainger Hall, Room 1185\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nLearn what BadgerVC is all about! We’ll share our mission, how to get involved, and upcoming events. Great for anyone curious about venture capital, startups, or joining the club. Come chat & connect!\n\nView Event →", "char_len": 2151, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::10", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 10, "text": "2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Grainger Hall, Room 1185\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nLearn what BadgerVC is all about! We’ll share our mission, how to get involved, and upcoming events. Great for anyone curious about venture capital, startups, or joining the club. Come chat & connect!\n\nView Event →\n\n![Entrepreneurship Org Fair](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1756868243212-NJM8J51AUU36I89VIOGL/ECB+building.jpg)\n\nSep\n\n12\n\n# Entrepreneurship Org Fair\n\n* Friday, September 12, 2025\n* 4:00 PM\n\n6:00 PM\n* ECB Building\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n* What to Expect:\n* 🚀 Network with founders, investors, and builders\n* 🤝 Connect with student orgs, accelerators, and VC groups\n* 🌍 Explore social impact & innovation initiatives\n* 📚 Discover campus and community entrepreneurial resources\n\nView Event →\n\n![Wisconsin School of Business Org Fair](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1756753805883-G5Y1ITKKWPF9B6GPZS89/wsb+exterior.jpg)\n\nSep\n\n8\n\n# Wisconsin School of Business Org Fair\n\n* Monday, September 8, 2025\n* 4:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* Wisconsin School of Business\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nCome meet us at our booth in the Wisconsin School of Business Org Fair! Members of BadgerVC will be present to answer any important questions you might have.\n\nView Event →\n\n#### **Some of our favorite past events!**\n\n![Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us &amp; What's Next]()\n\nMar\n12\n\nMarch 12, 2026\n\nStartup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next\n\nMarch 12, 2026\n\nMarch 12, 2026\n\n![Students in VC Panel ]()\n\nFeb\n26\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\nStudents in VC Panel\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\n#### **Fall ‘25 - VC 101 Series**\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics]()\n\nOct\n23\n\nOctober 23, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\nOctober 23, 2025\n\nOctober 23, 2025\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence]()\n\nOct\n9\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics &amp; Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse]()\n\nSep\n25\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics & Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\nSeptember 25, 2025", "char_len": 2220, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::11", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 11, "text": "9, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics &amp; Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse]()\n\nSep\n25\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics & Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\n#### **Thank you to each of our speakers who have shared their time and insights with BadgerVC!**\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/6561f7ed-c793-4c16-aa36-75385a1ddd43/0+%284%29.png)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/18f03352-0d3c-4ea8-8fc5-fff28b5ed17c/0+%283%29.png)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/c128e0df-9f2a-427a-b30d-f6bfdab81aa1/1740174669921.jpeg)\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/new-page\n\n## Connect With Us As….\n\n## A Student\n\nHave specific questions about what BadgerVC offers? Fill out the form below to reach out and have your questions answered!\n\n## An Industry Professional\n\nInterested in engaging with UW’s student VC community? Fill out the email form to get in contact with a BadgerVC representative!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/membership\n\n# Membership\n\nOur membership application for Spring semester has closed.\n\nMembers are welcome to apply during our next cycle in Fall ‘26!\n\nPlease reach out to badgervc@gmail.com with any questions on member requirements or applications!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/team-3\n\n## Our Team\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/6e2ae391-42cd-4b59-a233-567425678335/Caleb_LinkedIn.jpeg)\n\n#### Caleb Su\n\nPresident\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/d7556a1d-32d6-47a2-bea8-392b2c77bfda/Elliot_LinkedIn.jpeg)\n\n#### Elliot Miller\n\nVP Finance\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/63e86a12-6749-40a4-9f4d-d6ffdc9e0302/1759085070717.jpg)\n\n#### Rayna Onyegbula\n\nCo-VP of Marketing\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/060a6825-143a-4832-b0b8-d756fe548604/IMG_1166+%281%29.png)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/da6370f6-53c4-4088-a026-81fa88de8a6a/1761660448262.jpg)\n\n#### Dhanya Babu\n\nCo-VP of Marketing", "char_len": 2297, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::12", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 12, "text": "Dhanya Babu\n\nCo-VP of Marketing\n\n#### Have **ideas for innovative VC programming** or a strong interest in startups and investing?\n\n#### We encourage you to connect with us.\n\n#### Our board is **committed to expanding** and creating new roles for students who are eager to develop, execute, and lead new initiatives as we grow.\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/end-of-sem-social\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# End of Sem Social!\n\n* Thursday, April 23, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nMark your calendar for BadgerVC’s end of sem social!!\n\nMore details to come!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nApril 16\n\n## Investment Memo Workshop\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/end-of-sem-social?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:69d69d77fdd3132be7cadc28@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260408T183100Z\nDTSTART:20260423T230000Z\nDTEND:20260424T000000Z\nSUMMARY:End of Sem Social!\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/investment-memo-workshop\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Investment Memo Workshop\n\n* Thursday, April 16, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nInvestment memos are a key tool that venture capital firms use to evaluate startups and communicate investment decisions.\n\nIn this workshop, BadgerVC will guide you through the structure of a strong memo and show you how to write effective one-pagers.\n\nWhether you’re preparing for interviews or case competitions, this session will help you build a structured approach to analyzing startups and communicating persuasive recommendations.\n\nThis is a valuable skill for developing your perspective on different industries and emerging startups!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nApril 9\n\n## BadgerVC Career Trek!\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nApril 23\n\n## End of Sem Social!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/investment-memo-workshop?format=ical", "char_len": 1882, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::13", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 13, "text": "is a valuable skill for developing your perspective on different industries and emerging startups!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nApril 9\n\n## BadgerVC Career Trek!\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nApril 23\n\n## End of Sem Social!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/investment-memo-workshop?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:69d69a60dd64a6292fd48620@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260408T183111Z\nDTSTART:20260416T230000Z\nDTEND:20260417T000000Z\nSUMMARY:Investment Memo Workshop\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/badgervc-career-trek\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# BadgerVC Career Trek!\n\n* Thursday, April 9, 2026\n* 8:00 AM\n\n6:00 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nBadgerVC members will head to Chicago to explore careers in venture capital, visiting 3–4 firms across the city!\n\nMembers will\n\n* hear directly from investors and operators about their career paths\n* build connections,\n* and get a behind-the-scenes look at how early-stage companies are evaluated and supported\n\nThis is a great opportunity to better understand the VC ecosystem, ask questions in a small-group setting, and gain insight into full-time career paths in startups and investing!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nMarch 12\n\n## Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nApril 16\n\n## Investment Memo Workshop\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/badgervc-career-trek?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:69c2156dd18a2938d7d726e5@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260408T183127Z\nDTSTART:20260409T130000Z\nDTEND:20260409T230000Z\nSUMMARY:BadgerVC Career Trek!\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/startup-signals\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next\n\n* Thursday, March 12, 2026\n* 5:30 PM\n\n6:30 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n2025 reshaped how founders build and how investors deploy, and the lessons are still unfolding.", "char_len": 1991, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::14", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 14, "text": "[page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/startup-signals\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next\n\n* Thursday, March 12, 2026\n* 5:30 PM\n\n6:30 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n2025 reshaped how founders build and how investors deploy, and the lessons are still unfolding.\n\nBadgerVC and Badger Future Founders (BFF) are teaming up to bring you two people with front-row seats:\n**Grant Watkin****s** — from Gener8tor, working directly with early-stage founders navigating launches, traction, and the real grind of building\n**Mason Co****ok** — founder of Mastercraft Ventures, who completed fundraising in early 2025 and is actively shaping what smart early-stage investing looks like right now\n\nDuring the event, we’ll discuss:\n• What separated startups that gained traction from those that stalled.\n• What investors are looking for at pre-seed and seed today.\n• How AI is changing the cost and speed of building.\n• What the fundraising environment looks like as we enter 2026.\n\nRSVP here! **https://lnkd.in/ggXruqMW**\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nMarch 5\n\n## BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nApril 9\n\n## BadgerVC Career Trek!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/startup-signals?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:69c20f14516b91485c81e5a6@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260324T041748Z\nDTSTART:20260312T223000Z\nDTEND:20260312T233000Z\nSUMMARY:Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us &\\; What's Next\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/badgervc-x-career-engagement-studio\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio\n\n* Thursday, March 5, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin BadgerVC for a hands-on session with a representative from the Wisconsin School of Business Career Engagement Studio!\n\nLearn how to craft a standout resume, refine your cover letter, and strengthen your communication skills to stand out in competitive recruiting processes. Bring a physical or digital copy of your resume for live reviews!\n\nSee you there!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nFebruary 27\n\n## VC Networking Event (StratoVC)\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nMarch 12\n\n## Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next", "char_len": 2238, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::15", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 15, "text": "communication skills to stand out in competitive recruiting processes. Bring a physical or digital copy of your resume for live reviews!\n\nSee you there!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nFebruary 27\n\n## VC Networking Event (StratoVC)\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nMarch 12\n\n## Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/badgervc-x-career-engagement-studio?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:69c213eb01481820e4f72080@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260324T043818Z\nDTSTART:20260306T000000Z\nDTEND:20260306T010000Z\nSUMMARY:BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-networking-event-stratovc\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# VC Networking Event (StratoVC)\n\n* Friday, February 27, 2026\n* 3:30 PM\n\n5:30 PM\n\n* Tech Exploration Lab\n  1403 University Avenue\n  Madison, WI, 53715\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nInterested in raising capital?\n\nWant to pursue a career in venture capital?\n\n🚀 Join Strato VC’s first-ever venture capital networking event! We’re partnering with some of Madison’s leading VC & entrepreneurship student organizations, including **BadgerVC**, **UW Tech Exploration Lab**, **Transcend UW**, and **Women in Entrepreneurship - UW**, to bring valuable connections to innovation-minded students.\n\n🤝 Student attendees will have the opportunity to connect with leading professionals in Wisconsin, with backgrounds in venture capital, VC law, entrepreneurship, and more!\n\nStay Tuned: Professional partner announcements are coming soon!\n\n🔗 RSVP now: **https://luma.com/fxixeluz**\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nFebruary 26\n\n## Students in VC Panel\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nMarch 5\n\n## BadgerVC x Career Engagement Studio\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-networking-event-stratovc?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:699767383cfd5a3feee992d9@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260219T194443Z\nDTSTART:20260227T213000Z\nDTEND:20260227T233000Z\nSUMMARY:VC Networking Event (StratoVC)\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:Tech Exploration Lab\\, 1403 University Avenue\\, Madison\\, WI\\, 537\n15\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR", "char_len": 2239, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::16", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 16, "text": "Networking Event (StratoVC)\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:Tech Exploration Lab\\, 1403 University Avenue\\, Madison\\, WI\\, 537\n15\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/students-in-vc-panel\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Students in VC Panel\n\n* Thursday, February 26, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for our Students in VC Panel, where UW students with venture capital internship experience share their firsthand insights.\n\nPanelists will discuss:\n\n* How they landed their VC internships\n* What the recruiting & interviewing process looked like\n* What their day-to-day work involved\n* And what skills mattered most!\n\nThis is a great opportunity to ask questions, learn from your peers, and gain practical insights into breaking into VC as a student.\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nFebruary 19\n\n## Member Kickoff 🎉\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nFebruary 27\n\n## VC Networking Event (StratoVC)\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/students-in-vc-panel?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:698a31df4132c529aca77e95@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260324T040613Z\nDTSTART:20260227T000000Z\nDTEND:20260227T010000Z\nSUMMARY:Students in VC Panel\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/member-kickoff\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Member Kickoff 🎉\n\n* Thursday, February 19, 2026\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* Room # will be released to members\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nAll accepted members, join us for our first official meeting!\n\nGet to know your fellow members and dive into what’s coming this semester.\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nFebruary 16\n\n## Application Acceptances Released\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nFebruary 26\n\n## Students in VC Panel\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/member-kickoff?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:6973f9c4804c06216fceeb1c@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260123T225602Z\nDTSTART:20260220T000000Z\nDTEND:20260220T010000Z\nSUMMARY:Member Kickoff ð\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:Room # will be released to members\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR", "char_len": 2142, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
