8 State Street\n  Madison, WI, 53703\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/f2aab440-2ae2-4c65-af31-5f5fddbcc671/BadgerVC+Qdoba+Fundraiser+Design.png)\n\nGrab a bite to eat & support BadgerVC! Swing by the State street Qdoba between 4-8PM on Monday, January 26th.", "char_len": 2144, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::20", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 20, "text": "(map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/f2aab440-2ae2-4c65-af31-5f5fddbcc671/BadgerVC+Qdoba+Fundraiser+Design.png)\n\nGrab a bite to eat & support BadgerVC! Swing by the State street Qdoba between 4-8PM on Monday, January 26th.\n\nYou can order online and enter the digital coupon code **QDOBAGIVES** or show the BadgerVC Qdoba Flyer in store. BadgerVC will receive 25% of sales - we appreciate your support!\n\n*You can also find this flyer on our Instagram page @badgervc\\_ for your convenience.*\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 24\n\n## Inside a Venture-Backed Startup: A Recruiting & Networking Event with Traba\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nJanuary 29\n\n## BBA Organization Fair\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/applications-open?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:6973c1def96add59dab57aa1@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260123T185933Z\nDTSTART:20260126T220000Z\nDTEND:20260127T020000Z\nSUMMARY:Qdoba Fundraiser\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:Qdoba\\, 548 State Street\\, Madison\\, WI\\, 53703\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/inside-a-venture-backed-startup-a-recruiting-networking-event-with-traba\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Inside a Venture-Backed Startup: A Recruiting & Networking Event with Traba\n\n* Friday, October 24, 2025\n* 5:00 PM\n\n6:00 PM\n\n* Discovery to Product Building\n  1403 University Avenue\n  Madison, WI, 53715\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nThis Friday, October 24th at 5:00 PM, **BadgerVC** and **Transcend UW** will be hosting an exclusive session at 1403 University Avenue. All majors (and interested UW students are welcome!)\n\n**Traba** is a fast-growing startup backed by over $45M in funding from leading investors including Khosla Ventures, Founders Fund, and General Catalyst. Traba is a workforce management platform that connects businesses with vetted hourly workers, helping companies fill shifts efficiently.\n\nWe’ll hear directly from **Noah Thurer** (Growth Operations @ Traba) about what it’s like to work at a high-growth startup, navigate rapid expansion, and build a career in a fast-paced, venture-backed environment.\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 24\n\n## Fall Social!\n\nNext", "char_len": 2290, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::21", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 21, "text": "fill shifts efficiently.\n\nWe’ll hear directly from **Noah Thurer** (Growth Operations @ Traba) about what it’s like to work at a high-growth startup, navigate rapid expansion, and build a career in a fast-paced, venture-backed environment.\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 24\n\n## Fall Social!\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nJanuary 26\n\n## Qdoba Fundraiser\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/inside-a-venture-backed-startup-a-recruiting-networking-event-with-traba?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:68fa3ed4d040bc3d07ca3814@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260324T040942Z\nDTSTART:20251024T220000Z\nDTEND:20251024T230000Z\nSUMMARY:Inside a Venture-Backed Startup: A Recruiting & Networking Event wi\nth Traba\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:Discovery to Product Building\\, 1403 University Avenue\\, Madison\\,\nWI\\, 53715\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/fall-social\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Fall Social!\n\n* Friday, October 24, 2025\n* 2:00 PM\n\n3:00 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nTake a break and join **BadgerVC** for our Fall Social - come enjoy some cookies and chat with other BadgerVC members + exec members!\n\nCasual & and open to all BadgerVC members!\n\nLocation is in Flare!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 23\n\n## VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nOctober 24\n\n## Inside a Venture-Backed Startup: A Recruiting & Networking Event with Traba\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/fall-social?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:68f688b59743545dcc3accbf@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20251023T144139Z\nDTSTART:20251024T190000Z\nDTEND:20251024T200000Z\nSUMMARY:Fall Social!\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-101-lecture-3-term-sheets-fund-mechanics\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\n* Thursday, October 23, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  Madison, WI, 53715\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an in-depth session with Richelle Martin as we break down the key mechanics behind venture capital deals and fund operations.", "char_len": 2241, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::22", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 22, "text": "October 23, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  Madison, WI, 53715\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an in-depth session with Richelle Martin as we break down the key mechanics behind venture capital deals and fund operations.\n\nWe'll explore term sheet basics (the key elements of an investment agreement), portfolio strategy, the roles of different investors when structuring deals, and fund governance.\n\nThis is a great session to learn about the building blocks of a venture capital deal, and grow your understanding of VC fund operations. See you there!\n\n* Posted In: VC 101\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 21\n\n## Team Leads Due Diligence Workshop\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nOctober 24\n\n## Fall Social!\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events?category=VC+101\n\n#### **View upcoming events here!** Check out what we have planned next:\n\nFiltering by: “VC 101”\n\n---\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326432550-6QK0PXRK6I541EV5NHF6/IMG_2120.jpg)\n\nOct\n\n23\n\nVC 101\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\n* Thursday, October 23, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an in-depth session with Richelle Martin as we break down the key mechanics behind venture capital deals and fund operations.\n\nWe'll explore term sheet basics (the key elements of an investment agreement), portfolio strategy, the roles of different investors when structuring deals, and fund governance.\n\nThis is a great session to learn about the building blocks of a venture capital deal, and grow your understanding of VC fund operations. See you there!\n\nView Event →\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326450303-KKPW91UTFU2HVLNLIDRC/IMG_2119.jpg)\n\nOct\n\n9\n\nVC 101\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\n* Thursday, October 9, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an engaging session with Christian Kaczmarczyk, Principal at Third Prime, as he shares how VCs discover and assess promising startups.", "char_len": 2262, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::23", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 23, "text": "2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\n* Thursday, October 9, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an engaging session with Christian Kaczmarczyk, Principal at Third Prime, as he shares how VCs discover and assess promising startups.\n\nDeal Sourcing: How investors identify opportunities through networks, accelerators, and outreach.\n\nDue Diligence: The process of digging deeper into a startup’s market, financials, team, and product to decide if it’s worth investing in.\n\nThis session offers a practical inside look at the VC decision process, and a first hand look at Third Prime's process. See you there!\n\nView Event →\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics &amp; Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/1774326471867-4W99IPC59D7ZZ56JEQ0X/IMG_2118.jpg)\n\nSep\n\n25\n\nVC 101\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics & Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\n* Thursday, September 25, 2025\n* 6:30 PM\n\n7:30 PM\n* Grainger Hall, Room 1175\n  (map)\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for **VC 101: Intro to VC Basics + Recruiting**with Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\nThursday, Sept 25 | 6:30 - 7:30 PM at Grainger Hall Room 1175\n\nHear from Jonathon Horne, Managing Director of Idea Fund, and Sri Manikandan, UW student and current Idea Fund intern.\n\n* Learn the basics of venture capital\n* What investors look for\n* What founders should know about raising funding\n* And VC myths!\n\nPlus, get an inside look at Idea Fund, network with fellow students, **and explore opportunities to work with startups and VCs!**This session is open to **ALL students** - no experience required. RSVP **here** (resume upload is optional).\n\n\\*\\*Future events will be for BadgerVC Members only\n\nView Event →\n\n#### **Some of our favorite past events!**\n\n![Startup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us &amp; What's Next]()\n\nMar\n12\n\nMarch 12, 2026\n\nStartup Signals: What 2025 Taught Us & What's Next\n\nMarch 12, 2026\n\nMarch 12, 2026\n\n![Students in VC Panel ]()\n\nFeb\n26\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\nStudents in VC Panel\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\n#### **Fall ‘25 - VC 101 Series**\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics]()\n\nOct\n23\n\nOctober 23, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\nOctober 23, 2025", "char_len": 2290, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::24", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 24, "text": "2026\n\n![Students in VC Panel ]()\n\nFeb\n26\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\nStudents in VC Panel\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\nFebruary 26, 2026\n\n#### **Fall ‘25 - VC 101 Series**\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics]()\n\nOct\n23\n\nOctober 23, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\nOctober 23, 2025\n\nOctober 23, 2025\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence]()\n\nOct\n9\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\nOctober 9, 2025\n\n![VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics &amp; Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse]()\n\nSep\n25\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\nVC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics & Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\nSeptember 25, 2025\n\n#### **Thank you to each of our speakers who have shared their time and insights with BadgerVC!**\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/6561f7ed-c793-4c16-aa36-75385a1ddd43/0+%284%29.png)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/18f03352-0d3c-4ea8-8fc5-fff28b5ed17c/0+%283%29.png)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/68a73793f0a9f73543a6d916/c128e0df-9f2a-427a-b30d-f6bfdab81aa1/1740174669921.jpeg)\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-101-lecture-3-term-sheets-fund-mechanics?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:68bc80c8a759c40d3299d7ca@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260528T015302Z\nDTSTART:20251023T230000Z\nDTEND:20251024T000000Z\nSUMMARY:VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\\, Madison\\, WI\\, 5371\n5\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/team-leads-due-diligence-workshop\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# Team Leads Due Diligence Workshop\n\n* Tuesday, October 21, 2025\n* 7:00 PM\n\n8:00 PM\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\n**Session 1: 10/21**\n\n**Session 2: 10/28**\n\nDuring this session, you'll be introduced to a real startup and guided through the process of conducting due diligence.\n\nOur team leads will first walk members through a Due Diligence presentation, and then members will be paired up and assigned a specific area of the company to analyze, with plenty of support from our team leads if needed.", "char_len": 2263, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::25", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 25, "text": "a real startup and guided through the process of conducting due diligence.\n\nOur team leads will first walk members through a Due Diligence presentation, and then members will be paired up and assigned a specific area of the company to analyze, with plenty of support from our team leads if needed.\n\nThis is a low-pressure, learning focused environment! Team leads will be available throughout to provide guidance and answer questions.\n\nYou’ll also have time to complete your due diligence section asynchronously, before meeting again the following Tuesday (10/28)\n\nQuestions? Shoot us a message in Flare!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 16\n\n## How to Think Like an Investor\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nOctober 23\n\n## VC 101 Lecture 3: Term Sheets & Fund Mechanics\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/team-leads-due-diligence-workshop?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:68f685d06070ec3422af5464@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20251020T195205Z\nDTSTART:20251022T000000Z\nDTEND:20251022T010000Z\nSUMMARY:Team Leads Due Diligence Workshop\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/ikwgruuq3xpnzp32naqf3ou2qoe4y2\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# How to Think Like an Investor\n\n* Thursday, October 16, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:30 PM\n\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  Madison, WI, 53715\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nHow to Think Like an Investor\n**Featuring: Angel Padulo, Founder, Angel Investor, and Chief Operating Officer at Treasure Coast Ventures**\nDiscover what truly resonates with investors in Angel Padulo’s session on thinking like an investor - especially when presenting to VCs. Understanding what matters most to investors is essential for any founder looking to secure funding.\n\nLearn what makes a compelling pitch deck, convinces stakeholders, and positions a startup for success.\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 9\n\n## VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nOctober 21\n\n## Team Leads Due Diligence Workshop\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/ikwgruuq3xpnzp32naqf3ou2qoe4y2?format=ical", "char_len": 2107, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::26", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 26, "text": "pitch deck, convinces stakeholders, and positions a startup for success.\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 9\n\n## VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nOctober 21\n\n## Team Leads Due Diligence Workshop\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/ikwgruuq3xpnzp32naqf3ou2qoe4y2?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:68bdb15515ba0d27a0437ddf@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260528T015302Z\nDTSTART:20251016T230000Z\nDTEND:20251017T003000Z\nSUMMARY:How to Think Like an Investor\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\\, Madison\\, WI\\, 5371\n5\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-101-lecture-2-deal-flow-diligence\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\n\n* Thursday, October 9, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  Madison, WI, 53715\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nJoin us for an engaging session with Christian Kaczmarczyk, Principal at Third Prime, as he shares how VCs discover and assess promising startups.\n\nDeal Sourcing: How investors identify opportunities through networks, accelerators, and outreach.\n\nDue Diligence: The process of digging deeper into a startup’s market, financials, team, and product to decide if it’s worth investing in.\n\nThis session offers a practical inside look at the VC decision process, and a first hand look at Third Prime's process. See you there!\n\n* Posted In: VC 101\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nOctober 2\n\n## VC Q&A w/ Liam Krut, Investment Partner at Reinforced Ventures\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nOctober 16\n\n## How to Think Like an Investor\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-101-lecture-2-deal-flow-diligence?format=ical\n\nBEGIN:VCALENDAR\nVERSION:2.0\nPRODID:-//Squarespace Inc/Squarespace 6//v6//EN\nBEGIN:VEVENT\nUID:68bc7d4a7389475758b251e0@squarespace.com\nDTSTAMP:20260528T015302Z\nDTSTART:20251009T230000Z\nDTEND:20251010T000000Z\nSUMMARY:VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\\, Madison\\, WI\\, 5371\n5\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-101-lecture-2-deal-flow-diligence-9yneh\n\nBack to All Events", "char_len": 2290, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "badger-vc::27", "doc_slug": "badger-vc", "chunk_index": 27, "text": "101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence\nGEO:40.720756;-74.000761\nLOCATION:BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\\, Madison\\, WI\\, 5371\n5\\, United States\nEND:VEVENT\nEND:VCALENDAR\n\n## [page] https://www.badgervc.com/events/vc-101-lecture-2-deal-flow-diligence-9yneh\n\nBack to All Events\n\n# VC Q&A w/ Liam Krut, Investment Partner at Reinforced Ventures\n\n* Thursday, October 2, 2025\n* 6:00 PM\n\n7:00 PM\n\n* BadgerVC Members - location is in our Flare!\n  Madison, WI, 53715\n  United States\n  (map)\n\n* Google Calendar\n\nICS\n\nCurious about what it’s really like to work in VC? Join us for an open virtual Q&A with Liam Krut, Investment Partner at Reinforced Ventures, a firm investing at the frontier of robotics, biotech, and engineering.\n\nThis is a great opportunity to hear first-hand insights and words of advice, and ask any burning questions!\n\nWe’re excited to see you there!\n\nPrevious\n\nPrevious\n\nSeptember 25\n\n## VC 101 Lecture 1: VC Basics & Recruiting w/ Idea Fund of La Crosse\n\nNext\n\nNext\n\nOctober 9\n\n## VC 101 Lecture 2: Deal Flow & Diligence", "char_len": 1046, "id": 16, "source": "BadgerVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://www.badgervc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "capital-entrepreneurs::0", "doc_slug": "capital-entrepreneurs", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "## [page] https://capitalentrepreneurs.com\n\n# Community for Madison Founders\n\nWe, Capital Entrepreneurs, unite under the shared purpose of fostering a culture of support, collaboration, and growth. Together, we overcome obstacles, celebrate successes, and navigate the complexities of entrepreneurship. We pledge to extend a hand to all, regardless of their stage in the journey, embracing diversity of ideas and experiences. With empathy as our guide and innovation as our compass, we strive to build a network where every entrepreneur finds a home, a mentor, and a friend.\n\nOur monthly meetups are hosted by various members of our community, offering a unique flavor each time. Founder Day, our annual highlight, is a large-scale gathering that brings together as many founders as possible in one exciting day, celebrating our collective entrepreneurial spirit and achievements.\n\nJoin the Community\n\n![](https://capitalentrepreneurs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Icons_GroupChat-e1715200454221-1024x856.png)\n\n## Upcoming Events\n\nThere are currently no events.\n\n## Upcoming Events\n\nHost a Meetup\n\n## Madison Startup Resources\n\nNew to the Madison Startup scene? We’ve curated a list of resources in town specifically with founders in mind.\n\n#### Events\n\n![](https://capitalentrepreneurs.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/startup_showcase.jpg)\n\n#### Co-Working Spaces\n\n![StartingBlock Lobby](https://capitalentrepreneurs.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/LOBBY-2-1024x683.jpeg)\n\n#### Accelerators\n\n![](https://capitalentrepreneurs.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/gener8tor.jpg)\n\nView All Resources\n\n## [page] https://capitalentrepreneurs.com/founder-day\n\n13 â 14 May 2026\n\n![](https://framerusercontent.com/images/fzMtoxQk2xOMI9NO4fHOvkbpbs.svg?width=454&height=139)\n\nMadison, WI\n\n8 DAYS | 17 HOURS | 20 MIN | 0 SEC\n\nGet Registered\n\n![](https://frame