ng sessions around business models, interviewing potential customers and developing an elevator speech\n\nACCESS\n\nGet access to world-class content in a safe, friendly and fun environment\n\nACCOUNTABILITY\n\nWe work with you to identify your next critical milestone and develop a plan, budget and timeline to tackle it.\n\nNETWORKING", "char_len": 2199, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::32", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 32, "text": "models, interviewing potential customers and developing an elevator speech\n\nACCESS\n\nGet access to world-class content in a safe, friendly and fun environment\n\nACCOUNTABILITY\n\nWe work with you to identify your next critical milestone and develop a plan, budget and timeline to tackle it.\n\nNETWORKING\n\nJoin our vibrant community with weekly networking opportunities and a dedicated space to work.\n\n![StartingBlock Illustration.png](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_1635bd9f6c4245619e352b0411616729~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_29,h_18,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_1635bd9f6c4245619e352b0411616729~mv2.png)\n\n### Be in the know\n\nJoin our email list to stay up to date on all program announcements!\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/midwest-housing-accelerator\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/11062b_1d5fe2371f3a4d2caf40a1b369f55c01f000.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_83,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/11062b_1d5fe2371f3a4d2caf40a1b369f55c01f000.jpg)\n\n## Wisconsin's\n\n# HOUSING       SHORTAGE\n\n## The Housing Industry's Resistance to Change\n\nThe housing industry, while facing a critical shortage of homes, ironically struggles to embrace innovative solutions that could alleviate the problem. The way homes are built in the United States has remained largely unchanged for decades, resulting in a 50% decline in productivity since 1968. This reluctance to adopt new technologies and approaches has left the industry grappling with an aging workforce, soaring construction costs, and a backlog of nearly $3 trillion in unmet housing needs. This resistance to change, coupled with outdated building codes and a complex web of regulations, creates significant barriers for companies seeking to revolutionize home construction and address the urgent need for more affordable and sustainable housing.\n\n> Since 1984, the US House Sales Price to Income Ratio Has Jumped 5.8x\n\nZillow, 2024\n\n> Wisconsin's 20 Largest Counties Underproduced Over 26,000 Housing Units From 2006-2023\n\nUS Census Bureau data 2006-2023\n\n> 88% of General Contractors Had a Hard Time Filling Craft Positions\n\n2023 Associated General Contractors Survey", "char_len": 2186, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::33", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 33, "text": "Sales Price to Income Ratio Has Jumped 5.8x\n\nZillow, 2024\n\n> Wisconsin's 20 Largest Counties Underproduced Over 26,000 Housing Units From 2006-2023\n\nUS Census Bureau data 2006-2023\n\n> 88% of General Contractors Had a Hard Time Filling Craft Positions\n\n2023 Associated General Contractors Survey\n\n![2025 housing accelerator speakers.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_fa975f4e31794190a073d065f7643cba~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_366,h_489,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/2025%20housing%20accelerator%20speakers.jpg)\n\n2025 | Building Tomorrow's House | Six Part Speaker Series\n\nThe series brought together architects, engineers, 3D concrete builders, academics, and construction professionals to explore how modular construction, robotics, and advanced manufacturing could address Wisconsin's housing shortage.\n\nSessions featured international perspectives from Swedish modular manufacturer Lindbacks and 3D printing pioneer COBOD International, regulatory and permitting deep-dives with state legislators and local building officials, design methodology workshops, and manufacturing and supply chain analysis from the USDA Forest Products Lab.\n\nThe series surfaced critical challenges and opportunities that now form the foundation for our 2026 Housing Materials and Production Innovation Challenge.\n\n# LET'S DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT.\n\nAnnouncing the AEC Housing Innovation Challenge, with support from American Family Dreams Foundation and the Small Business Administration.\n\n![am fam dreams.png](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_05b43973f29f48ed8ae4794a174ca9be~mv2.png/v1/crop/x_72,y_296,w_965,h_458/fill/w_293,h_139,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/am%20fam%20dreams.png)\n\nProblem Statements that emerged out of the 2025 work included:\n\n​\n\n* How might we standardize or streamline the regulatory pathway for innovative construction methods?\n* How might we design manufacturing systems that can produce building components at scale using regional materials and just-in-time delivery?\n* How might we create mass customization systems that allow meaningful design variation while maintaining production efficiency?\n* How might we reduce the time between factory completion and occupancy-ready installation?\n\n​\n\nWhere is this heading?​​", "char_len": 2280, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::34", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 34, "text": "regional materials and just-in-time delivery?\n* How might we create mass customization systems that allow meaningful design variation while maintaining production efficiency?\n* How might we reduce the time between factory completion and occupancy-ready installation?\n\n​\n\nWhere is this heading?​​\n\n![students (3).png](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_99b85a7c53a84cf2834a9aa1847c3426~mv2.png/v1/crop/x_43,y_71,w_496,h_338/fill/w_391,h_267,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/59b71f_99b85a7c53a84cf2834a9aa1847c3426~mv2.png)\n\n## 2026 | Housing Materials and Production Innovation Challenge\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/lunch-and-learn-tactical-skills-series\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_4a0be4416f5b44bdb3199cae0c7321e0~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_36,h_18,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_4a0be4416f5b44bdb3199cae0c7321e0~mv2.png)\n\n# Lunch & Learn\n\n### TACTICAL SKILLS SERIES\n\n### BY STARTINGBLOCK\n\nThe Lunch & Learn: Tactical Skills Series is six comprehensive, monthly, professional development workshops, from April through September 2026. This dynamic program bringing in local experts across the areas entrepreneurs need most: HR and employment law, contracts, marketing and positioning, sales, branding, and financial fundamentals.\n\nJoin us from 12-1PM in StartingBlock's 2nd floor classroom of learning that could revolutionize your business approach! This series includes interactive Q&A sessions, valuable networking opportunities, and lunch.\n\n#### 2026 Expert Speakers\n\n![Keri Allard Headshot](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_5419c37aa56346c5a35c5608aa11613a~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_313,h_313,fp_0.52_0.43,q_75,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_5419c37aa56346c5a35c5608aa11613a~mv2.png)\n\nAPRIL 14 | KERI ALLARD\n\nBuild It Right: HR & Payroll\nfor Growing Startups\n\nRSVP NOW\n\n![Lane Rideout Headshot](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_d974c47ef8b647adb5cb8b1ca37121c8~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_314,h_313,fp_0.53_0.44,q_75,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_d974c47ef8b647adb5cb8b1ca37121c8~mv2.png)\n\nMAY 7 | LANE RIDEOUT\n\nBound for Success: Important Contracts to Protect You and Your Startup\n\nRSVP NOW", "char_len": 2183, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
