~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_49,h_49,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_efa959c18c924852b2ed359068cd0938~mv2.png)\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_4c736f46d62f4ad5a04516a33e503ae5~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_49,h_49,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_4c736f46d62f4ad5a04516a33e503ae5~mv2.png)", "char_len": 2219, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::52", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 52, "text": "1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_efa959c18c924852b2ed359068cd0938~mv2.png)\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_4c736f46d62f4ad5a04516a33e503ae5~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_49,h_49,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_4c736f46d62f4ad5a04516a33e503ae5~mv2.png)\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_6c5548161e09470197a90f491faa03cb~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_49,h_25,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_6c5548161e09470197a90f491faa03cb~mv2.png)\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_d8417ed043bd4cc693c30d17f41f5b24~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_49,h_49,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_d8417ed043bd4cc693c30d17f41f5b24~mv2.png)\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_c3eb4e010e824a9eb22b4532c75ca432~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_49,h_43,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_c3eb4e010e824a9eb22b4532c75ca432~mv2.png)\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_0a777dd169ec4f7dadda7aecaf605bcc~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_147,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_0a777dd169ec4f7dadda7aecaf605bcc~mv2.jpg)\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_067dad62a5eb4efeb82aaa6f728c5bf3~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_56,h_56,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/397fdf_067dad62a5eb4efeb82aaa6f728c5bf3~mv2.png)\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/jobs\n\n## Community Job Board\n\nStartingBlock community members are hiring! Do you have a job posting? Let us know.\n\nSUBMIT A JOB POSTING\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/account/my-account\n\n## Sign Up\n\nAlready a member?Log In\n\nSign up with Google\n\nSign up with Facebook\n\nor\n\nSign up with email\n\nor sign up with\n\nSign up to this site with a public profile.Read more\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/submit-a-job-opening\n\n## Submit your job opening to our Job Board\n\nJob Title\n\nLocation\n\nJob Type\n\nWhat type of Job is this\n\nIn Person / Remote\n\nIs the position open for remote work\n\nJob Description\n\nJob Requirements\n\nEnter the Job Requirements\n\nNormal Text\n\nTitleSubtitleNormal Text\n\nAbout Us\n\nApplication Link\n\nListing Expiration Date \\* required\n\nSUBMIT YOUR JOB LISITNG\n\nYour job listing has been submitted , it will be live on our website soon.", "char_len": 2291, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::53", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 53, "text": "position open for remote work\n\nJob Description\n\nJob Requirements\n\nEnter the Job Requirements\n\nNormal Text\n\nTitleSubtitleNormal Text\n\nAbout Us\n\nApplication Link\n\nListing Expiration Date \\* required\n\nSUBMIT YOUR JOB LISITNG\n\nYour job listing has been submitted , it will be live on our website soon.\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/team-3\n\n![c6ae45_361a00dd99f349d1a6f630658b454b29~mv2.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_d2f987f3a6ab40cd9209df1a2e19c07f~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_120,h_60,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_d2f987f3a6ab40cd9209df1a2e19c07f~mv2.jpg)\n\n# Our Interns\n\n##### Supporting the next generation of professionals\n\n## Current Intern\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_34f1ec7094f445ed9d98b6d9eba501b3~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_225,h_225,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/GettyImages-591216789.jpeg)\n\n##### Julia Vondrak\n\n###### Sales and Marketing Intern\n\nJulia is a Strategic Communications student at UW–Madison with certificates in Entrepreneurship and Digital Media Analytics. She brings hands-on experience in social media management, content creation, and digital marketing from roles at Fiskars, the Sandra Rosenbaum School of Social Work, and the Wisconsin State Capitol.\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/julia-vondrak/\n\n## Past Interns\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_c398d206abc748c59340f1ad5d024a22~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_56,h_56,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/GettyImages-591216789.jpeg)\n\n##### Anna Maples\n\n###### Event Planner\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/anna-maples-224442232/\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_6a4f5d3673ba4a13990fa47328771119~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_45,h_56,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/GettyImages-591216789.jpg)\n\n##### Maciej Czerlonko\n\n###### Law and Entrepreneurship Fellow\n\nMaciej is an Associate Attorney with Russell Law Offices, primarily working with agricultural families, rural landowners, and small business owners. His practice focuses on business law, estate planning, and civil litigation, where he helps clients navigate everything from complex contracts and property transitions to dispute resolution and estate administration.\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/maciej-czerlonko-a81570155/", "char_len": 2297, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::54", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 54, "text": "small business owners. His practice focuses on business law, estate planning, and civil litigation, where he helps clients navigate everything from complex contracts and property transitions to dispute resolution and estate administration.\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/maciej-czerlonko-a81570155/\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_a2375a84693d487a91705c21f8e3ae68~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_37,h_56,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/GettyImages-591216789.jpeg)\n\n##### Jake Kealy\n\n###### Law and Entrepreneurship Fellow\n\nSince interning at StartingBlock, Jake has worn many hats—finishing law school, serving as a Judicial Intern for Judge William M. Conley in the Western District of Wisconsin, and becoming an attorney. Upon graduating from the University of Wisconsin Law School, Jake began his career as a Naval Officer and Judge Advocate General (JAG), now serving as Defense Counsel at DSO West in San Diego, California, representing sailors on some of their toughest days.\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/jakekealy/\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_dd905da8581f4001a2c417237da06f2e~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_56,h_54,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/GettyImages-591216789.jpeg)\n\n##### Kate Gehringer\n\n###### Events Intern\n\nWith a passion for entrepreneurship, Kate began her career in software sales after graduating from UW–Madison in 2024. At Box, she grew from an SDR to supporting enterprise outbound strategies, gaining hands-on experience with the entire sales cycle and Fortune 500 clients. Now at Uber as an SMB Account Executive, Kate manages her own book of business - an outcome that mirrors the entrepreneurial drive that first inspired her career in sales.\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/kate-gehringer/\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_6bf15eb9d9bc432d97c2887c4cb33d9a~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_56,h_56,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/GettyImages-591216789.jpeg)\n\n##### Avery Liggon\n\n###### Marketing Intern\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/avery-liggon/\n\nEmail\n\ninfo@mysite.com\n\nCall\n\n123-456-7890\n\nFollow", "char_len": 2110, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::55", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 55, "text": "Avery Liggon\n\n###### Marketing Intern\n\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/avery-liggon/\n\nEmail\n\ninfo@mysite.com\n\nCall\n\n123-456-7890\n\nFollow\n\n* ![Facebook](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/0fdef751204647a3bbd7eaa2827ed4f9.png/v1/fill/w_25,h_25,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/0fdef751204647a3bbd7eaa2827ed4f9.png)\n* ![Twitter](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c7d035ba85f6486680c2facedecdcf4d.png/v1/fill/w_25,h_25,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/c7d035ba85f6486680c2facedecdcf4d.png)\n* ![LinkedIn](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/6ea5b4a88f0b4f91945b40499aa0af00.png/v1/fill/w_25,h_25,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/6ea5b4a88f0b4f91945b40499aa0af00.png)\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/tour\n\n###### 🔴 6 tours booked this week | ⭐ 5/5 stars on Google\n\n![PXL_20240814_151959278.MP.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_74bf2c5d86804661a734cc975c99ffaa~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_77,h_58,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_74bf2c5d86804661a734cc975c99ffaa~mv2.jpg)\n\n## Book Your StartingBlock Tour | Coworking Space Madison, WI\n\n###### Join 140 companies and 425+ entrepreneurs at Wisconsin's highest-rated coworking space in Madison, WI — the startup hub for remote workers, small businesses, and founders.\n\nBOOK A TOUR HERE\n\nThis is a 45-minute tour, not a sales pitch. See the space, ask questions, decide if it's right for you. No commitment, no awkwardness—promise.\n\n## About Us\n\n###### StartingBlock is Madison's premier coworking space and entrepreneur hub, designed for startups, small businesses, and remote workers across Madison, Wisconsin.\n\n![coworking space](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_bad427fb49ce43dfad2a82145e8cb476~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_98,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_auto/c6ae45_bad427fb49ce43dfad2a82145e8cb476~mv2.jpg)\n\n![cafe](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_91e22c683c29402cbabf4ea79f7a2a9d~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_83,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_auto/c6ae45_91e22c683c29402cbabf4ea79f7a2a9d~mv2.jpg)", "char_len": 2073, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::56", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 56, "text": "8,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_auto/c6ae45_bad427fb49ce43dfad2a82145e8cb476~mv2.jpg)\n\n![cafe](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_91e22c683c29402cbabf4ea79f7a2a9d~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_83,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_auto/c6ae45_91e22c683c29402cbabf4ea79f7a2a9d~mv2.jpg)\n\n![private office](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/ac6072_4528e8694589434786fa90cb33557bea~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_98,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_auto/ac6072_4528e8694589434786fa90cb33557bea~mv2.jpg)\n\n![coworking space](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_bad427fb49ce43dfad2a82145e8cb476~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_98,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_auto/c6ae45_bad427fb49ce43dfad2a82145e8cb476~mv2.jpg)\n\n1/10\n\n#### Why the best teams choose our coworking space\n\nCompared to the National Brands\n\n##### Us\n\n##### Other Coworking Spaces\n\n#### Our Coworking Space\n\n* 24/7 access + security\n* Free on-street parking\n* 140-company network\n* Private offices\n* Flex desks for individuals and growing teams\n* Conference rooms included\n* Multiple community activities every month\n* Free coffee, always\n* Access to $1M of free credits, perks and discounts\n\n#### Other Coworking spaces\n\n* Close at 5pm\n* $50+/month in hidden fees\n* Mostly remote workers, no community\n* Desks only\n* Pay hourly for conference rooms\n* Pay for coffee\n* No startup perks or network\n\nScott Forester, Madison WI\n\n> \"StartingBlock is an amazing coworking space and is by far the best one in Madison! It's much more than just a coworking space - it offers many amenities and is also a great place to network and meet some of Madison's finest entrepreneurs.\"\n\nTherese Merkel, Madison, WI\n\n> \"StartingBlock is hands-down my favorite co-working space in Madison, WI! As an entrepreneur, I’ve worked from quite a few spots over the years, and StartingBlock knows what's up.\"\n\nTyler Waite, Madison, WI\n\n> \"StartingBlock is one of, if not 𝘵𝘩𝘦 cornerstone of entrepreneurship in Madison. Our company’s first “professional” office was at StartingBlock, since their location, pricing, and community programming makes them really unique.\"", "char_len": 2121, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::57", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 57, "text": "and StartingBlock knows what's up.\"\n\nTyler Waite, Madison, WI\n\n> \"StartingBlock is one of, if not 𝘵𝘩𝘦 cornerstone of entrepreneurship in Madison. Our company’s first “professional” office was at StartingBlock, since their location, pricing, and community programming makes them really unique.\"\n\n![Entrepreneur working on laptop at Flex Desk in StartingBlock coworking space](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_c20ee4b31ceb4d98b69503ca70e8ea1c~mv2.jpg/v1/crop/x_372,y_0,w_873,h_1080/fill/w_375,h_464,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Entrepreneur%20working%20on%20laptop%20at%20Flex%20Desk%20in%20StartingBlock%20coworking%20space.jpg)\n\n#### Flex Membership\n\n##### From $180/Month\n\n##### ​\n\nLearn More\n\n![126396996_1666188440207057_4735683413406](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_f2cb299f725d4dfc8cdcb9dfc8ee6810~mv2.jpg/v1/crop/x_37,y_0,w_873,h_1080/fill/w_375,h_464,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/126396996_1666188440207057_4735683413406.jpg)\n\n#### Reserved Membership\n\n##### From $300/Month ​\n\nLearn More\n\n![An-entrepreneurial-workspace-scene-featuring-diverse-individuals-collaborating-in-a-modern](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_0f84eea24c5b436e9bc2372280b5247e~mv2.png/v1/crop/x_202,y_0,w_621,h_768/fill/w_375,h_464,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/An-entrepreneurial-workspace-scene-featuring-diverse-individuals-collaborating-in-a-modern.png)\n\n#### Private Office\n\n##### Rates based on size ​\n\nLearn More\n\nAnchor 1\n\nWhat should I expect on the tour?\nYour 45 minute tour\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\nMemberships\n\n### Is StartingBlock a good fit for remote workers or small businesses?\n\nAbsolutely. Whether you're a remote worker looking for a professional coworking space in Madison, WI, a freelancer needing a day pass, or a small business ready for a private office — StartingBlock has a membership that fits.\n\n### What should I expect on the tour?\n\nYour 45-minute tour includes a walkthrough of all spaces, explanation of membership options, and time for your questions. Absolutely no pressure.\n\n### How much does membership cost?\n\nFlex desks start at $180/month, reserved desks at $300/month, and private offices from $700/month. We'll discuss what fits your needs and budget.", "char_len": 2271, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::58", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 58, "text": "a walkthrough of all spaces, explanation of membership options, and time for your questions. Absolutely no pressure.\n\n### How much does membership cost?\n\nFlex desks start at $180/month, reserved desks at $300/month, and private offices from $700/month. We'll discuss what fits your needs and budget.\n\n### Can I try it before committing?\n\nYes! We offer $20 day passes. Tour first, then try a day pass to see if you love it.\n\n### What if I need to reschedule my tour?\n\nNo problem—you'll get a confirmation email with a reschedule link. Life happens!\n\n### Is there parking?\n\nYes, there is free on street parking on both Main St and Livingston.\n\n## Meet Our Team\n\nGet to know the team behind StartingBlock - Madison's Startup Hub. Our diverse team is dedicated to supporting and empowering entrepreneurs on their journey to success.\n\n![scott-mosley-startingblock-aug2023.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_a4f34fe7bfc2425d9ba36ae5c44a33f6~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_150,h_150,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/scott-mosley-startingblock-aug2023.jpg)\n\nScott Mosley\n\nCEO\n\n* ![LinkedIn](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/11062b_60c5fc4a3ecd49f2a697206b09eeace1~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_23,h_23,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/11062b_60c5fc4a3ecd49f2a697206b09eeace1~mv2.png)\n\n![Ott-37_edited.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/397fdf_7e3a54abbf3b4c97b8000a9e0bd5272c~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_150,h_150,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Ott-37_edited.jpg)\n\nBeth Ott\n\nDirector of Programs\n\n* ![LinkedIn](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/11062b_60c5fc4a3ecd49f2a697206b09eeace1~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_23,h_23,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/11062b_60c5fc4a3ecd49f2a697206b09eeace1~mv2.png)\n\n![Presenter in front of an audience at StartingBlock networking event](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_166d1ded113143ccba676cf97429145a~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_82,h_61,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_166d1ded113143ccba676cf97429145a~mv2.png)\n\n##### Download\n\n## The Coworking Comparison Worksheet\n\nUse this handy tool to help keep track of the best coworking location for you and your team\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/the-conversation-on-a-plane-that-changed-everything\n\nSearch", "char_len": 2284, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::59", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 59, "text": "Download\n\n## The Coworking Comparison Worksheet\n\nUse this handy tool to help keep track of the best coworking location for you and your team\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/the-conversation-on-a-plane-that-changed-everything\n\nSearch\n\nSome companies come to StartingBlock wide-eyed and just getting started. Earthling Interactive came in with 20 years of history behind them, and a very different kind of story to tell.\n\nThe Madison-based technology consultancy has been a fixture in the Madison community since 1999, when two founders launched what would eventually become one of the region's most adaptable tech firms. Through the rise of the internet, the shift to software-as-a-service, and now the AI revolution, Earthling has done something most companies don't: they've kept evolving.\n\n![Earthling Interactive Logo](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_ec793bbc22cb445391480eed9a9b81ae~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_80,h_80,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/2faa74_ec793bbc22cb445391480eed9a9b81ae~mv2.png)\n\nEarthling Interactive Logo\n\n\"We've seen a lot in 25-plus years,\" says the company's CEO, John Samuelson. \"But AI is certainly adapting faster than anything we've seen.\"\n\nEarthling Interactive specializes in helping businesses in construction, agriculture, and higher education untangle the mess of manual processes, legacy systems, and disconnected tools that slow teams down. Their work includes custom software, systems integration, and now AI agent solutions.\n\n## **The Right Space at the Right Time**\n\nWhen Earthling joined StartingBlock in 2021, it wasn't because they needed mentorship or a launch pad. Coming out of COVID, the team had transitioned to a hybrid work model and simply didn't need their full office space, but they still wanted something private and professional.\n\n\"It fit perfectly for us at that time,\" John explains. \"And having some established, mature businesses in the mix was a nice difference.”", "char_len": 1975, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::60", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 60, "text": "the team had transitioned to a hybrid work model and simply didn't need their full office space, but they still wanted something private and professional.\n\n\"It fit perfectly for us at that time,\" John explains. \"And having some established, mature businesses in the mix was a nice difference.”\n\nThat mix turned out to be one of the most valuable parts of the experience. Running into other business leaders in the hallway, sharing a floor with companies across wildly different industries, attending Lunch with the Founder events, it was the kind of organic connection that only happens when you put curious people in the same room.\n\nThe practical side mattered too. Saving on rent during a pivotal transition period freed up capital to invest in people, including the roles needed to step into the next chapter of the business.\n\n## **A $50 Million Conversation at 30,000 Feet**\n\nTwenty-five years of business means twenty-five years of stories. But one stands out.\n\nBack around 2006 or 2007, before Earthling had made its full leap into web application development, the CEO at the time struck up a conversation with a stranger on a plane. That stranger mentioned a startup in Wausau building a healthcare industry application, a project they weren't interested in taking on. They passed along a name. Earthling followed up, went through the sales cycle, beat out competing firms, and landed the project.\n\nIt was their entry point into web development. That Wausau company eventually sold for $50 million. Earthling stayed on as a service partner through it all.\n\n\"It was just a conversation on an airplane,\" the CEO says. \"One thing led to another. We never pass up an opportunity to have a conversation.\"\n\nIt's a story that doubles as a business philosophy, and one that takes on new meaning as AI reshapes how work gets done. \"The charismatic, relationship-based person is going to increase in value,\" he says. \"AI is going to infiltrate a lot of industries, but the person who can step in, connect, and fill any room, that's irreplaceable.\"\n\n## **What's Next**", "char_len": 2064, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::61", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 61, "text": "that takes on new meaning as AI reshapes how work gets done. \"The charismatic, relationship-based person is going to increase in value,\" he says. \"AI is going to infiltrate a lot of industries, but the person who can step in, connect, and fill any room, that's irreplaceable.\"\n\n## **What's Next**\n\nEarthling is leaving StartingBlock on a high note. In April 2025, the company was acquired by Lift Consulting, a Madison firm with complementary strengths and shared ownership vision. The two companies are now moving under one roof (still in Madison), and one direction.\n\n![CEO John Samuelson in front of Suite door](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_d4c4bf58fb3a4691aa467d336db1c94d~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_147,h_110,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/2faa74_d4c4bf58fb3a4691aa467d336db1c94d~mv2.jpeg)\n\nCEO John Samuelson in front of Suite door\n\nThe team recently hired a Chief AI Officer, a former Earthling employee from 2011–2018 who spent years deep in enterprise AI work before returning to the fold. It's the kind of full-circle moment that a 25-year company earns.\n\nAs for the five-year vision? Simple: become the staple name people in Madison, Dane County, and across Wisconsin think of when they think process automation and custom AI.\n\n\"I want to be that trusted company that makes an impact across this industry,\" John says. \"We've made strides. Now it's about making that brand even stronger.\"\n\nStartingBlock gave Earthling Interactive the space, literally and figuratively, to keep building. And for a company that's been reinventing itself since before most of today's startups existed, that's saying something.\n\n*Earthling Interactive is based in Madison, Wisconsin. Learn more at**earthlinginteractive.com**.*\n\n![StartingBlock Madison Receives $75,000 SBA Growth Accelerator Fund Competition Award]()\n\n![Victoria Thayer headshot and Novii CPA logo]()\n\n![ALL3D overview image with chair and the three options for a 3D mockup: 3D model, lifestyle images, and all view in room,]()\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/how-one-student-built-the-sf-effect-in-madison\n\nSearch\n\n*This post was written by* *Armaan Jain**, founder of Priority and Priority Labs. The views expressed are his own.*", "char_len": 2243, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::62", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 62, "text": "for a 3D mockup: 3D model, lifestyle images, and all view in room,]()\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/how-one-student-built-the-sf-effect-in-madison\n\nSearch\n\n*This post was written by* *Armaan Jain**, founder of Priority and Priority Labs. The views expressed are his own.*\n\n![Armaan Jain, founder of priority, who built the SF effect in Madison WI](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_451ac8ec84814c2aaf59d872ed2fbc2c~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_49,h_61,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/59b71f_451ac8ec84814c2aaf59d872ed2fbc2c~mv2.png)\n\nFor years, the narrative around building something has been the same: leave. Go to SF. Go to NYC. Go anywhere but here. All the talented people in every other city pack up and move to one of two places because that's where the energy is.\n\nBut the real SF effect isn't about geography. It's about density. **It's about the belief that the people next to you are building things that matter.** And here's what I realized: every city has the talent. The founders, engineers, artists, musicians, and creators are everywhere. They're just scattered, stuck in their own buildings, their own majors, their own circles. Everyone's growing, but there's no shared ecosystem.\n\nSo I decided to start with UW-Madison, with the people around me, and see what would happen if we built *'it'* ourselves. That's why I created Priority Labs, the in-person extension of Priority, the productivity app I'm building to help people follow through on what matters.\n\nPriority Labs is a 9-day sprint for student founders, creators, engineers, and musicians, a place for anyone building anything. The first cohort ran April 10-19, 2026, with 16 students from UW-Madison.\n\nThe same day I thought of the idea, I thought, “Why would anyone trust ME to lead this?” I wasn't sure anyone would show up.\n\nBut people did, and what happened surprised even me.\n\nThe format itself was extremely simple but intentional. Each day started at 7 am with accountability: everyone stood up in front of the group, shared what they'd done the day before, and committed to what they'd do that day. Then I told them to get to work and collaborate however they wanted, and what surprised me was that people chose to talk to people doing completely different things.", "char_len": 2296, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::63", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 63, "text": "everyone stood up in front of the group, shared what they'd done the day before, and committed to what they'd do that day. Then I told them to get to work and collaborate however they wanted, and what surprised me was that people chose to talk to people doing completely different things.\n\nThe only thing everyone had in common was that they cared about what they were making. No prizes. No competition. No lectures. There was only one rule, and it was simple: show up every morning at 7 AM, work, and share your story at a final showcase hosted by StartingBlock Madison.\n\nAs you can imagine, getting college students to wake up at 7 AM every day for 9 days is hard. **But people kept showing up.** And that’s the part I didn't fully understand when I designed this: support & accountability from other real people that you have a connection with is 10x better than self-discipline.\n\nOne student started a new personal brand, and within days, was interviewing the CEO of Vortex Optics. Some built their first apps and prepared for pitch competitions. Another hit the road to perform original music with her band. Someone ran their first marathon. And a lot more. All of this happened because of who was in the room.\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_3caa3e0c100d48699689da5a18d6e670~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_147,h_111,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/59b71f_3caa3e0c100d48699689da5a18d6e670~mv2.jpeg)\n\nThose 9 days felt like 30, but soon, it was showcase day, the most nerve-wracking day of my college life. I felt like I owed it to everyone to make this successful. And soon, 12 people showed up at StartingBlock to share what they'd built with their friends, family, and the broader community.\n\nIf you'd asked me a month before whether I was capable of putting this together, I would have said no. Watching the cohort present, I was genuinely happy for the community we built and the progress everyone made. What I ended up building was one of the most action-oriented groups of people I’ve seen at UW-Madison.\n\nThen it ended. And here's the part I'm still thinking about.", "char_len": 2106, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::64", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 64, "text": "I would have said no. Watching the cohort present, I was genuinely happy for the community we built and the progress everyone made. What I ended up building was one of the most action-oriented groups of people I’ve seen at UW-Madison.\n\nThen it ended. And here's the part I'm still thinking about.\n\nFor 9 days, something happened that I couldn't have created on my own. The morning routines, the mutual accountability, the contagious momentum, worked. But on day 10, the cohort dispersed. Soon, people went back to their lives. The energy faded the way it always does after intense experiences. I got to thinking...how could I keep that action oriented energy alive?\n\nThat's the question I'm trying to answer with Priority.\n\n> Priority Labs proved that **people change because of the people around them**, not because of better task management. The reason Priority Labs worked is that everyone in the room was becoming someone, and was doing it with others. Priority is built around the same idea: every habit you complete, every commitment you follow through on, is evidence of who you're becoming.\n\nThe app isn't a replacement for what happened at Priority Labs, but it's the closest thing I know how to build right now. You can see what we’re building at Priority at www.joinpriority.app and what the inaugural cohort built on the Labs page.\n\nFinally, we’re running Cohort 2 in Fall 2026. If you want to be part of building this as a mentor, a connection, or just by spreading the word, please reach out. We'd love your help making the next cohort even better.\n\nTo everyone who showed up, to Beth Ott and StartingBlock Madison for hosting and supporting us, and to my team at Priority who helped make it happen: thank you, from the bottom of my heart. You proved something we needed to see proven. Now we know it works. The only question is how big this can get and how many people we can help.\n\n![The Conversation on a Plane that Changed Everything]()\n\n![How to Find Your First Customer]()\n\n![From Two Desks to a Warehouse: Accessible Housing's Next Chapter]()\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/how-to-find-your-first-customer\n\nSearch", "char_len": 2156, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::65", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 65, "text": "get and how many people we can help.\n\n![The Conversation on a Plane that Changed Everything]()\n\n![How to Find Your First Customer]()\n\n![From Two Desks to a Warehouse: Accessible Housing's Next Chapter]()\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/how-to-find-your-first-customer\n\nSearch\n\nI am going to let you in on a secret that the startup industry on LinkedIn or X or Instagram has managed to obscure under approximately forty-seven frameworks, three online courses, and a podcast episode recorded in someone's closet.\n\nAre you ready?\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_31599ea115214a1facea4f887ce244f8~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_147,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/59b71f_31599ea115214a1facea4f887ce244f8~mv2.jpg)\n\n**Go talk to people. Then ask them to buy the thing.**\n\nThat's it. That is the whole secret.\n\nI know. I know. You were expecting something more sophisticated -- a funnel, a persona worksheet, a go-to-market strategy deck with a TAM/SAM/SOM slide that you had to Google how to build. And look, those things have their place. But none of them will find you a single customer. You will.\n\nEvery week I talk to founders who are waiting. Waiting for the product to be perfect, waiting for the website to be done, waiting for the pitch to be tight enough to take to investors. And somewhere in that waiting, they have convinced themselves that a venture capitalist is going to look at their idea -- their idea, with no customers, no revenue, no proof that a single human being on Earth will hand over money for it -- and write them a check.\n\nI need you to hear this clearly: that is not how it works.\n\n> Investors fund traction. Traction is made by founders who go out and do the thing. And the thing... the actual, unglamorous, not-covered-in-a-podcast-episode thing... is selling.\n\nSo. How do you find your first customer?", "char_len": 1881, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::66", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 66, "text": "them a check.\n\nI need you to hear this clearly: that is not how it works.\n\n> Investors fund traction. Traction is made by founders who go out and do the thing. And the thing... the actual, unglamorous, not-covered-in-a-podcast-episode thing... is selling.\n\nSo. How do you find your first customer?\n\n**You start having conversations.** Not product demos. Not pitch meetings. Conversations. You find the people who have the problem you think you're solving and you ask them about their lives. You figure out who actually makes the purchasing decision, because the person who feels the pain and the person who signs the check are often not the same person, and confusing the two will cost you months. You get specific about who your market actually is, not who you wish it were.\n\nAnd then (*and this is the part people skip*) you ask for the sale.\n\nYou will probably not be great at this at first. That's not a flaw in your character; it's just where you are in your learning curve. **Selling is a skill, and skills are built through repetition and feedback,** not through watching other people do it on YouTube. You are going to have awkward conversations. You are going to misread rooms. You are going to walk away from a meeting unsure of what just happened. This is fine. This is, in fact, the point.\n\nThe founders who figure out their first customer faster are not the ones who planned better. They're the ones who were willing to be bad at selling for a little while -- who treated every conversation as data, adjusted, and went back out. They strengthened their selling muscles the only way muscles get strengthened.\n\nNobody is born knowing how to sell. Nobody funds a good idea without proof it can sell. And nobody is coming to find your first customer for you.\n\nNow go have some conversations.\n\n![The Conversation on a Plane that Changed Everything]()\n\n![How One Student Built the SF Effect in Madison]()\n\n![From Two Desks to a Warehouse: Accessible Housing's Next Chapter]()\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/from-two-desks-to-a-warehouse-accessible-housing-s-next-chapter\n\nSearch", "char_len": 2107, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::67", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 67, "text": "Conversation on a Plane that Changed Everything]()\n\n![How One Student Built the SF Effect in Madison]()\n\n![From Two Desks to a Warehouse: Accessible Housing's Next Chapter]()\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/post/from-two-desks-to-a-warehouse-accessible-housing-s-next-chapter\n\nSearch\n\nWhen David Gordon first sat down at StartingBlock Madison, he had one colleague, a growing portfolio of rental properties, and an idea that would quietly reshape how Madison thinks about accessible living. Today, as CEO of Accessible Housing, he's packing up that desk, and many others, not because things didn't work out, but because they worked out almost too well.\n\n![Accessible Housing's Office at StartingBlock Madison](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_b433c5fc7f87486eb8fd82b5d553505e~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_147,h_98,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/2faa74_b433c5fc7f87486eb8fd82b5d553505e~mv2.jpg)\n\nAccessible Housing's Office at StartingBlock Madison\n\n\"It's bittersweet,\" Gordon admits with a laugh.\n\nAccessible Housing specializes in building and modifying homes for people who need mid-fill accessible housing. This is a major niche that sits at the intersection of construction, community care, and smart urban development. Gordon started by buying houses to rent, stumbled into accessibility modifications, and never looked back. \"Never thought I'd have a construction company and get this far,\" he says.\n\nFrom two people to a team of ten, Accessible Housing has modified 70 homes across Madison. One of Gordon's proudest accomplishments has been building two-unit ADUs at a moment when Madison's zoning laws were just opening the door for that kind of development. Being first to market with that model wasn't just a business win. It meant community members got quality places to live sooner.\n\nStartingBlock, Gordon says, was the right place to grow. The energy, the network, the connections to community leaders, it all added up. \"Some of the nicest office space,\" he says, only half joking. \"The competitors kind of get blown out of the water.\" He also appreciated something more practical: the rent. Which matters when you're a two-person operation trying to stretch every dollar into something real.\n\n## Looking Ahead: Plans for Growth and Innovation", "char_len": 2297, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::68", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 68, "text": "space,\" he says, only half joking. \"The competitors kind of get blown out of the water.\" He also appreciated something more practical: the rent. Which matters when you're a two-person operation trying to stretch every dollar into something real.\n\n## Looking Ahead: Plans for Growth and Innovation\n\nBut now Accessible Housing needs a warehouse. Somewhere to store materials, run a cost-effective construction operation, and house a team that has outgrown a coworking desk. Gordon is candid that it's in a worse location and the offices are \"a little more sad.\" That honesty says something about what StartingBlock meant to the company's early years.\n\n![Group of smiling people in matching shirts holding a red ribbon at a ribbon-cutting ceremony. Fall trees and houses in the background.](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_6075ce2f822341efaf42bb8d4067ce75~mv2.webp/v1/fill/w_147,h_98,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/2faa74_6075ce2f822341efaf42bb8d4067ce75~mv2.webp)\n\nAccessible Housing WI\n\nLeaving, though, doesn't mean disappearing forever. Gordon is quick to point out that Accessible Housing will remain woven into the fabric of downtown Madison involved with and working closely with local leadership. \"We're still a big part of downtown,\" he says. The mission hasn't changed.\n\nIn five years, Gordon sees hundreds of units and a construction operation that runs efficiently, cost-effectively, and at scale. He wants Accessible Housing to be a permanent fixture in the community, not just a developer, but a neighbor.\n\nFor StartingBlock Madison, stories like David Gordon's are the whole point. Two people with a vision, a desk, and the right environment. A few years later, they have ten employees, 60-plus homes, and a warehouse to grow into.\n\nThat's not leaving. That's graduating.\n\n##\n\n![The Conversation on a Plane that Changed Everything]()\n\n![How One Student Built the SF Effect in Madison]()\n\n![How to Find Your First Customer]()\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/blog\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_0c90ebd092314f288fb10f5bc3b31311~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_100,h_63,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_0c90ebd092314f288fb10f5bc3b31311~mv2.jpg)\n\n# Community News", "char_len": 2258, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
