act@startingblockmadison.org.\n\nBy using our website, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to these Terms and Conditions.\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/frequently-asked-questions", "char_len": 2081, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::76", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 76, "text": "or concerns regarding these Terms and Conditions, please contact us at contact@startingblockmadison.org.\n\nBy using our website, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to these Terms and Conditions.\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/frequently-asked-questions\n\n![VI6A2920-scaled.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_3313bcc5eea1464bb238b13ecc1be9fd~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_54,h_36,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_3313bcc5eea1464bb238b13ecc1be9fd~mv2.jpg)\n\n### Frequently Asked Questions\n\n###### Membership\n\nWhat is StartingBlock Madison?\nStartingBlock Madison is a vibrant entrepreneurial hub and coworking space located in the heart of Madison, Wisconsin. It serves as a launchpad for startups, providing a supportive and collaborative environment for entrepreneurs, innovators, and small businesses to thrive.\n\nWho can join StartingBlock?\nStartingBlock is open to anyone interested in entrepreneurship, innovation, and coworking. Whether you're a solo entrepreneur, startup founder, freelancer, or a team member of an established business, you are welcome to become a member and utilize our workspace and community resources.\n\nHow can I become a member of StartingBlock?\nBecoming a member of StartingBlock is easy! You can visit our website at www.startingblockmadison.org and click on the \"Join\" or \"Membership\" section to explore the membership options. Choose the plan that suits your needs, and you can sign up online.\n\nWhat are the different membership plans available?\nStartingBlock offers various membership plans to cater to different needs. Our plans typically include options for hot desks in the coworking area, dedicated desks, and private offices.\n\nCan I try out StartingBlock before becoming a member?\nYes, you can! StartingBlock offers a free trial day for individuals who are interested in becoming members. This allows you to experience our coworking space, amenities, and community before making a commitment.\n\n###### Amenities", "char_len": 2017, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::77", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 77, "text": "offices.\n\nCan I try out StartingBlock before becoming a member?\nYes, you can! StartingBlock offers a free trial day for individuals who are interested in becoming members. This allows you to experience our coworking space, amenities, and community before making a commitment.\n\n###### Amenities\n\nWhat amenities does StartingBlock offer?\nStartingBlock offers a wide range of amenities to support your work and business needs. These include modern coworking spaces, private offices, meeting rooms, high-speed internet, printing facilities, coffee and refreshment areas, event spaces, and access to mentorship and networking opportunities.\n\nAre there any networking events or programs at StartingBlock?\nYes, we regularly host networking events, workshops, seminars, and panel discussions on various topics related to entrepreneurship, technology, and innovation. These events provide excellent opportunities to connect with like-minded individuals, investors, and potential partners.\n\nIs there parking available at StartingBlock?\nYes, StartingBlock offers monthly parking at the Livingston Street parking ramp for its members. You can find nearby parking options on our website or contact our team for more information.\n\n###### Event Spaces\n\nCan I book meeting rooms or event spaces at StartingBlock?\nYes, members and non-members can book meeting rooms and event spaces at StartingBlock. Our spaces are equipped with modern amenities and can be reserved by reaching out to our community team.\n\nCan I host my own events at StartingBlock?\nYes, members have the opportunity to host their events at StartingBlock . Whether it's a workshop, meetup, or networking event, we encourage our members to share their knowledge and expertise with the community.\n\n###### Community\n\nDoes StartingBlock offer any support for startups and entrepreneurs?\nAbsolutely! StartingBlock Madison provides a supportive ecosystem for startups and entrepreneurs. We offer mentorship programs, workshops, networking events, and access to a community of experienced individuals who can offer guidance and support.", "char_len": 2079, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::78", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 78, "text": "offer any support for startups and entrepreneurs?\nAbsolutely! StartingBlock Madison provides a supportive ecosystem for startups and entrepreneurs. We offer mentorship programs, workshops, networking events, and access to a community of experienced individuals who can offer guidance and support.\n\nDoes StartingBlock have a code of conduct?\nYes, StartingBlock maintains a code of conduct to ensure a respectful and positive environment for all members and visitors. By joining our community, you agree to abide by this code of conduct, which promotes collaboration, inclusivity, and professionalism.\n\nDoes StartingBlock offer any resources for funding or investment opportunities?\nWhile StartingBlock does not directly provide funding or investment opportunities, we do have a network of investors, mentors, and organizations that can assist startups in finding the resources they need.\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/offices\n\n![231224565_1874212136071352_7238802513537312405_n.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_eeeaeb1a4a3d40e486d1d0e0297a23f6~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_54,h_36,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_eeeaeb1a4a3d40e486d1d0e0297a23f6~mv2.jpg)\n\n# Available Offices\n\n## Amenities & Perks\n\nWhether you're just starting out or looking to scale, StartingBlock's memberships provide the flexibility and resources you need to grow your startup. Choose from a range of StartingBlock's coworking membership options that fit your budget and goals.\n\n![Website Icons-membership-01.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_59dcf556b9d249ea8ff2f2e73acce57c~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_121,h_121,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Website%20Icons-membership-01.jpg)\n\n3rd Floor Work Cafe\n\nEnjoy the views and open space of the 3rd Floor Cafe and Patio.\n\n![Website Icons-membership-04.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_0d521fd9e5c9432db5c7e0fbfcfeae91~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_121,h_121,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Website%20Icons-membership-04.jpg)\n\nIndoor Bike Storage + Showers\n\nRide your bike to work or take a noontime spin. We've got showers too.", "char_len": 2141, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::79", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 79, "text": "Bike Storage + Showers\n\nRide your bike to work or take a noontime spin. We've got showers too.\n\n![Website Icons-membership-02.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_7d1cf84041604337b4eb0a7e7bc4a82a~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_121,h_121,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Website%20Icons-membership-02.jpg)\n\nFree WiFi\n\nWe have blazing fast WiFi that can handle any video conference.\n\n![Website Icons-membership-06.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_2281888f4a53427eaf0966e28da07b7c~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_121,h_121,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Website%20Icons-membership-06.jpg)\n\nFree Printer + At Cost Large Scale Printing\n\nWe have onsite printing for small jobs and access to AmFam's print shop for large ones.\n\n![Website Icons-membership-03.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_3bcaa8450fa14d6ebf40bc3bd131099f~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_121,h_121,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Website%20Icons-membership-03.jpg)\n\nMail Box\n\nHave your mail sent to your own address and private mailbox.\n\n![Website Icons-membership-07.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_b7eae27e4fa2477c912c4bcb5c2c0546~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_121,h_121,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Website%20Icons-membership-07.jpg)\n\nCommunity\n\nWe have dozens of community events each month. Join us and grow your network.\n\n![Available June 1](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_f916f137a238415787965e5051ef422e~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_88,h_59,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/Image-empty-state.jpg)\n\nAvailable June 1\n\n## Suite 225\n\nThis modern 1000 square foot office space is designed to maximize functionality and comfort, featuring two private offices or breakout rooms that cater to diverse work needs. Situated on a prominent corner, the office benefits from significant natural light, creating an inviting and productive atmosphere.\n\nSize:\n\n1000\n\nMaximum number of desks:\n\n10\n\nVIEW DETAILS\n\n$3000\n\nPrice per month:", "char_len": 1991, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::80", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 80, "text": "featuring two private offices or breakout rooms that cater to diverse work needs. Situated on a prominent corner, the office benefits from significant natural light, creating an inviting and productive atmosphere.\n\nSize:\n\n1000\n\nMaximum number of desks:\n\n10\n\nVIEW DETAILS\n\n$3000\n\nPrice per month:\n\n![Available ASAP](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/ac6072_d8860db508b54a7488ab0e02074ed9fa~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_88,h_59,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/Image-empty-state.jpg)\n\nAvailable ASAP\n\n## Suite 406\n\nSpacious 710 sqft private office featuring an open layout, abundant natural light, and flexible workspace options for small teams.\n\nSize:\n\n710\n\nMaximum number of desks:\n\n6\n\nVIEW DETAILS\n\n$2200\n\nPrice per month:\n\n![Available Sept 1](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/2faa74_9b708aec04a443f198a3a41e1e839d2d~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_88,h_59,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,blur_2,enc_avif,quality_auto/Image-empty-state.jpg)\n\nAvailable Sept 1\n\n## Suite 237\n\nThis interior office is perfect for a small team of 6 or less.\n\nSize:\n\n615\n\nMaximum number of desks:\n\n6\n\nVIEW DETAILS\n\n$1500\n\nPrice per month:\n\nSEE MORE\n\nBOOK A TOUR\n\n## [page] https://www.startingblockmadison.org/leap-year-curriculum\n\n![Leap Year StartingBlock White](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_16ebf16298d6467bbd94688497ad5167~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_211,h_211,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Leap%20Year%20StartingBlock%20White.png)\n\n# Curriculum Details\n\nAt the heart of Leap Year is the desire to help you start your own business.\n\nAn alternative to more school.\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_30406f8ea3f4414d992ab4d13fbd9a82~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_600,h_100,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/59b71f_30406f8ea3f4414d992ab4d13fbd9a82~mv2.png)\n\n### PHASE 1 Weeks 1-4, Sept 2nd -Sept 26\n\n### PHASE 2 Weeks 5-12, Oct 6 -Dec 5\n\n### PHASE 3 Weeks 13-32, Jan 5th- May 25th\n\n### Find the Right Problem", "char_len": 1930, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::81", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 81, "text": "PHASE 1 Weeks 1-4, Sept 2nd -Sept 26\n\n### PHASE 2 Weeks 5-12, Oct 6 -Dec 5\n\n### PHASE 3 Weeks 13-32, Jan 5th- May 25th\n\n### Find the Right Problem\n\nEvery great business starts with a great problem. This phase is all about figuring out if your idea is actually worth pursuing. Through hands-on workshops, real convos with potential customers, and creative problem-solving, you'll test your assumptions and fine-tune your startup concept. Be ready to challenge what you think you know—by the end, you’ll have a sharper, more focused idea that’s ready to be tested.​\n\n​\n\nFounders will meet 9am-noon daily, with afternoon mentoring/small group work.\n\n​\n\nField Trip: We'll travel to Milwaukee to visit Microsoft AI Co-Innovation Labs.\n\nCohort Community Building:  We'll attend a Forward soccer game at Breese Stevens field, and take in some local music.\n\nMentorship Pairing: Once you have an idea, we'll pair you with a local mentor who can hold you accountable to your launch plan.\n\nPrize Opportunity: Participants will present their Lean Canvas, and the founder with the most creative business plan will win $250.\n\n### Test and Build\n\nNow it’s time to see if your idea really works. You’ll build a prototype, experiment with customer feedback, and tweak your business model based on what you learn. This phase is all about adapting, pivoting, and making your idea stronger. By the end, you’ll have a real, working business model and a clear understanding of who your customers are.​\n\n​\n\n​\n\n​\n\nFounders will meet 9am-noon daily with afternoons spent conducting customer outreach and discovery interviews.\n\n​\n\nField Trip: We'll travel to Platteville to visit the Huff Family Innovation Center.\n\nGuest Speakers: Shelby Olstad (Miggy's Bakes) and Ben Miller (Kwik Drip) share their startup stories.\n\nMonthly Challenges: Conducting customer interviews is paramount to building a successful business. But talking to people? SCARY. Let's do it together.\n\nPrize Opportunity:  Founders will pitch their business using a traditional pitch deck. Most compelling pitch deck wins $5,000.\n\n### Grow and Scale", "char_len": 2091, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::82", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 82, "text": "Challenges: Conducting customer interviews is paramount to building a successful business. But talking to people? SCARY. Let's do it together.\n\nPrize Opportunity:  Founders will pitch their business using a traditional pitch deck. Most compelling pitch deck wins $5,000.\n\n### Grow and Scale\n\nOver the next five months, you’ll keep leveling up your business with weekly workshops, expert mentors, and a supportive founder community. Whether you're working on getting more customers, locking in funding, or perfecting your brand, this phase is all about staying on track and making real progress. You’ll have the guidance and accountability to keep pushing forward and turning your startup into something real.​\n\n​\n\nFounders will meet weekly for accountability and workshops, but are expected to work based on their individualized  goals. For serious founders, this may mean 40+ hours of building per week.\n\n​\n\nField Trip: We'll travel to TitleTown Tech to hear about the businesses they're investing in.\n\nWorkshop: We'll deep dive into presentations, public speaking, and knowing your audience with expert public speakers.\n\nFinal Presentations: Choose between a pitch or a summary of learning. Invite your friends, and celebrate the launch of your new business.\n\nPrize Opportunity: The cohort will vote on the 'winner', or who should receive the last $5,000.\n\n### The Curriculum\n\nAsh Maurya’s LeanStack methodology is a structured approach to building successful businesses by focusing on rapid learning, customer validation, and minimizing waste. It’s grounded in Lean Startup principles and is designed to help entrepreneurs test ideas efficiently before investing significant time or money. Here’s why it’s a legit, proven method used by startups worldwide.\n\n​\n\n### 1. Start with a Problem, Not a Solution\n\nInstead of jumping straight to an idea, LeanStack forces entrepreneurs to deeply understand the problem they’re solving. This ensures they’re addressing a real market need rather than just a cool concept. In Leap Year, we spend FOUR WEEKS finding the right problem to solve.\n\n​\n\n### 2. Use the Lean Canvas", "char_len": 2114, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::83", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 83, "text": "of jumping straight to an idea, LeanStack forces entrepreneurs to deeply understand the problem they’re solving. This ensures they’re addressing a real market need rather than just a cool concept. In Leap Year, we spend FOUR WEEKS finding the right problem to solve.\n\n​\n\n### 2. Use the Lean Canvas\n\nMaurya created the Lean Canvas, a one-page business model tool that simplifies the traditional business plan. It helps founders quickly map out critical elements like their problem, target customers, and unique value proposition—without spending months writing a rigid business plan. Similar to a Business Model Canvas, a Lean Canvas approach breaks down a traditional business plan into bullet points and boxes, not paragraphs.\n\n​\n\n### ​\n\n​​​3. Test Before You Build\n\nRather than assuming a product will work, LeanStack emphasizes running small, low-cost experiments to validate key assumptions (do those people really want this feature?). This reduces the risk of failure and increases the chances of building something people actually want. We supplement Ash's work here with Testing Business Ideas by David Bland and Alex Osterwalder.\n\n​\n\n### 4. Traction Over Perfection\n\nMany entrepreneurs get stuck perfecting their product before launching. LeanStack teaches that traction (customer interest and engagement) matters more than perfection. Early feedback is crucial for shaping a successful business. We'll practice giving and receiving feedback, so founders get the most out of it.\n\n​\n\n### 5. Continuous Learning & Iteration\n\nStartups that succeed don’t get it right on the first try. LeanStack encourages rapid learning cycles—build, measure, learn—so businesses can adapt quickly based on real customer feedback. We'll figure out what to measure and how to keep track of it.\n\n### ​\n\n​", "char_len": 1791, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::84", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 84, "text": "5. Continuous Learning & Iteration\n\nStartups that succeed don’t get it right on the first try. LeanStack encourages rapid learning cycles—build, measure, learn—so businesses can adapt quickly based on real customer feedback. We'll figure out what to measure and how to keep track of it.\n\n### ​\n\n​\n\nLeanStack isn’t just a trendy startup idea—it’s based on real-world evidence from thousands of successful companies. It’s used by accelerators, universities, and even corporations to teach responsible entrepreneurship—a method that minimizes risk while maximizing learning. In short, LeanStack is a smart, validated approach to starting a business, and it teaches young entrepreneurs the critical skills of problem-solving, resilience, and customer focus—all essential for success in any field. Which is why StartingBlock uses it for all our accelerators and programming.\n\n![Heading (10).png](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_ea0d690926ae4274a9cf1beee6b40e96~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_473,h_473,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Heading%20(10).png)\n\nSign up\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_1b2b175f20d84408af5f5e1067794cd1~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_390,h_55,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/59b71f_1b2b175f20d84408af5f5e1067794cd1~mv2.png)\n\nPROGRAM TOPICS\n\n​\n\nFocus on the Problem, not the Solution\n\nCustomer Discovery\n\nValidation Tactics\n\nBuilding and Prototyping\n\nDesign Thinking\n\nMonetization Strategies\n\nFinancial Fundamentals\n\nBuilding a Standout Brand\n\nSocial Media Marketing and Gen Z\n\nStorytelling\n\nBootstrapping or Raising Money\n\nPresentations of Learning\n\nDemo Days\n\nResume Building and Marketing as a Solopreneur\n\n# By the end, you'll have...\n\n##### A Founder's Playbook\n\nA Lean Canvas, market analysis, and a validated business concept ready to launch.\n\n##### Hands-On Startup Skills\n\nCustomer interviewing, rapid prototyping, pitching, and the ability to turn ideas into action.\n\n##### A Powerful Network\n\nConnections to mentors, investors, and a community of like-minded student founders.\n\n##### A Certificate in Entrepreneurship\n\nProof that you didn't just study business-you built one.\n\n###### Meet your instructor, Beth.\n\n## The Instructor", "char_len": 2197, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::85", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 85, "text": "ability to turn ideas into action.\n\n##### A Powerful Network\n\nConnections to mentors, investors, and a community of like-minded student founders.\n\n##### A Certificate in Entrepreneurship\n\nProof that you didn't just study business-you built one.\n\n###### Meet your instructor, Beth.\n\n## The Instructor\n\n![20191002_164600.jpg](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_a9be66c726e748a7bd3ddc8ac9317faf~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_263,h_354,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/20191002_164600.jpg)\n\nBeth joined the StartingBlock team last year, and bringing her on board has been one of the best decisions we've ever made (psst, she’s also the one writing this). Since then, we’ve been able to launch our own programming, including a variety of accelerators and workshops.\n\n​\n\nWith a Master’s in Education and 17 years in the classroom, she knows how to design engaging, accessible sessions that make complex business concepts easy to grasp. Her ability to juggle all the moving pieces of our programs—while also keeping founders on track—has been a game changer.\n\n​\n\nThanks to her, we’ve guided 75+ founders through our own programs, made countless strategic connections, and built a stronger, more impactful community. When she’s not running workshops or matching founders with the right resources, she’s probably brainstorming new ways to level up StartingBlock’s offerings (or sneaking in a coffee break).\n\nBeth was an excellent teacher of this class. I really enjoyed the variety of class formats - instructional, workshops, mentoring, guest speakers, etc. It was 2 hours a week extremely well spent, and I loved the accountability it gave me to keep moving forward with building my business.\n\n— Andrea R., Associated Bank Fellowship\n\nThe Level Set workshop gave us a lot of helpful information about starting our business and a modern approach to getting it off the ground. Beth was very supportive of our process.\n\n— Rev R., Level Set\n\nAccept and Secure your spot with a down payment.\n\n## APR 22 MAY 15 JUN 11\n\n## INFO SESSIONS\n\n## APR\n\n## 12\n\n## APPLICATIONS OPEN\n\n## JUN\n\n## 15\n\n## APPLICATIONS CLOSE\n\n## JULY\n\n## 1\n\n## COHORT CHOSEN\n\n## 2\n\n## SEPT\n\n## FIRST DAY\n\nSIGN UP\n\nKeep an eye out for an invitation to interview in your inbox.", "char_len": 2244, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
