{"chunk_id": "starting-block-madison::110", "doc_slug": "starting-block-madison", "chunk_index": 110, "text": "images, and all view in room,](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/59b71f_d888b333935d43229fa9c2fd245bfb48~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_454,h_341,fp_0.50_0.50,q_95,enc_avif,quality_auto/59b71f_d888b333935d43229fa9c2fd245bfb48~mv2.webp)\n\n## StartingBlock Spotlight: Kaiser Pister CTO at ALL3D\n\nMar 25, 2025\n\n![10 Key Insights from Wisconsin Investors on Entrepreneurship, Startups, and Small Businesses](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_7127b092e3a0449681cc5c1b76319360~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_333,h_250,fp_0.50_0.50,q_30,blur_30,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_7127b092e3a0449681cc5c1b76319360~mv2.webp)![10 Key Insights from Wisconsin Investors on Entrepreneurship, Startups, and Small Businesses](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/c6ae45_7127b092e3a0449681cc5c1b76319360~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_454,h_341,fp_0.50_0.50,q_90,enc_avif,quality_auto/c6ae45_7127b092e3a0449681cc5c1b76319360~mv2.webp)\n\n## 10 Key Insights from Wisconsin Investors on Entrepreneurship, Startups, and Small Businesses\n\nJan 30, 2025", "char_len": 990, "id": 17, "source": "StartingBlock Madison", "type": "static_html", "category": "accelerator", "url": "https://www.startingblockmadison.org/"}
{"chunk_id": "startup-learning-community::0", "doc_slug": "startup-learning-community", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "## [page] https://www.housing.wisc.edu/undergraduate/communities/startup\n\n* How to Join\n* Seminar\n* Programming\n* Photos\n* Resources\n* Staff\n\n# StartUp Learning Community\n\n![StartUp logo](https://www.housing.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/168/2020/01/startup-logo-black.png)\n\n**Sellery Residence Hall**\n\n*(one floor)*\n\n65 residents\n\nMixed coed floor of doubles\n\n*(gender inclusive room options available)*\n\nStudents in over 70 different majors have been part of StartUp since its launch in 2007. If you are a doer and maker with big ideas, creativity, and who enjoys putting together teams, this learning community is for you. StartUp is a vibrant community of students that are a mix of engineers, writers, designers, musicians, biologists and business majors.\n\n**Sponsor:** Wisconsin School of Business | **Open to:** any major\n\n**Additional Fee:** $250 *(exception request form)*\n\n![StartUp Learning Community residents studying together in a lounge](https://www.housing.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/168/2023/03/startup-header-photo.jpg)\n\n## How to Join\n\nAll items must be completed by your due date *(May 1 for most admitted students)*. You can be assigned to any learning/theme community even if you did not preference it.\n\n1. Sign your University Residence Halls contract and submit your advance payment in My UW Housing.\n2. Rank the StartUp Learning Community first when you submit your hall preferences in My UW Housing.\n3. Prioritize learning communities over residence halls when you submit your hall preferences in My UW Housing.\n4. Indicate if you want a random or preferred roommate in My UW Housing, and create/join a roommate group if you have a preferred roommate*(s)*. Make sure all preferred roommates have matching preferences.\n\nBack to top\nBack to top\n\nquotation mark\n> Being a part of StartUp enabled me to attend exclusive events and meet the people who have done what I can’t wait to do.\n\nNathan E., StartUp Resident\n\n## Seminar", "char_len": 1959, "id": 11, "source": "Startup Learning Community", "type": "static_html", "category": "campus-portal", "url": "https://www.housing.wisc.edu/undergraduate/communities/startup/"}
{"chunk_id": "startup-learning-community::1", "doc_slug": "startup-learning-community", "chunk_index": 1, "text": "have a preferred roommate*(s)*. Make sure all preferred roommates have matching preferences.\n\nBack to top\nBack to top\n\nquotation mark\n> Being a part of StartUp enabled me to attend exclusive events and meet the people who have done what I can’t wait to do.\n\nNathan E., StartUp Resident\n\n## Seminar\n\n![ERLC residents studying in Sellery Hall](https://www.housing.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/168/2017/11/2009-11-17-erlc-studying-1-compressed-e1513884468825-600x201.jpg)\n\n### Introduction to Entrepreneurship\n\n**Management & Human Resources 322** | **3 credits**\n\nStartUp residents have the opportunity to enroll in a cutting-edge, three-credit course on entrepreneurship designed for those interested in learning more about starting their own ventures. Students do not need prior business or entrepreneurial experience and do not need to have immediate plans to become an entrepreneur. The course provides a general introduction to entrepreneurship as an economic phenomenon as well as a possible career option. The course covers a broad range of topics, including evaluating opportunities, building a team, testing for market validation, and financing a startup. Students participate in an entrepreneurial project during the course to apply course concepts in real-time.\n\nBack to top\nBack to top\n\n## Programming\n\n### Community Goals\n\n* Teach students to put their ideas into action through innovative thinking, analysis, and planning\n* Assist with harnessing key resources to make students’ ideas reality\n* Stress the importance of learning by doing\n* Help students create new sources of value *(profit/nonprofit, private/social good)*\n\nStartUp has acted as a springboard for many young entrepreneurs on campus. Thanks to the resources and education the community provides to residents, many have already started successful start-ups in the Madison area during their undergraduate experience. If you have an idea that you would like to see come to life, be sure to take advantage of access to funding for research opportunities with faculty from across campus, as well as Dream Big grants.\n\n### Events & Activities", "char_len": 2119, "id": 11, "source": "Startup Learning Community", "type": "static_html", "category": "campus-portal", "url": "https://www.housing.wisc.edu/undergraduate/communities/startup/"}
{"chunk_id": "startup-learning-community::2", "doc_slug": "startup-learning-community", "chunk_index": 2, "text": "start-ups in the Madison area during their undergraduate experience. If you have an idea that you would like to see come to life, be sure to take advantage of access to funding for research opportunities with faculty from across campus, as well as Dream Big grants.\n\n### Events & Activities\n\nThe 100-Hour Challenge is one of the most popular community highlights of the year. Challenging the inventiveness, resourcefulness, and creativity of students as they are required to create and pitch a valuable, innovative, or socially beneficial product or service using materials from UW-Madison SWAP, in only 100 hour’s time participants must upload either a digital photo or video of their invention for judging.\n\nStartUp also offers many other ways for residents to get involved by providing a forum for making connections and learning from others willing to share their experiences and guidance. Some have even spawned entrepreneurial ideas for residents that have led to using funds allocated within StartUp to assist students in creating their own business ventures. Other yearly signature events include:\n\n* Dream Big grants\n* Monthly community dinners with members of the Madison-area entrepreneurial community\n* Resume and elevator pitch workshops\n* Site visits to area entrepreneurship venues\n\nBack to top\nBack to top\n\n## Photos\n\n![ERLC members attend Procter and Gamble event](https://www.housing.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/168/2017/11/2012-03-21-erlc-procter-gamble-3-compressed.jpg)\n\n![ERLC residents participate in a 100 hour challenge](https://www.housing.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/168/2017/11/2017-11-09-erlc-100-hour-challenge-8-compressed-1500x1000.jpg)\n\n![ERLC residents studying in Sellery Hall](https://www.housing.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/168/2017/11/2009-11-17-erlc-sellery-studying-1-compressed.jpg)\n\n![ERLC residents participate in a 100 hour challenge](https://www.housing.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/168/2017/11/2017-11-09-erlc-100-hour-challenge-7-compressed-1500x1000.jpg)\n\nBack to top\nBack to top\n\n## Resources\n\n### INSITE Entrepreneurship Guide\n\nThe most authoritative source on campus for entrepreneurship resources.\n\n### StartUp Campus Partners", "char_len": 2201, "id": 11, "source": "Startup Learning Community", "type": "static_html", "category": "campus-portal", "url": "https://www.housing.wisc.edu/undergraduate/communities/startup/"}
{"chunk_id": "startup-learning-community::3", "doc_slug": "startup-learning-community", "chunk_index": 3, "text": "to top\nBack to top\n\n## Resources\n\n### INSITE Entrepreneurship Guide\n\nThe most authoritative source on campus for entrepreneurship resources.\n\n### StartUp Campus Partners\n\nStartUp is connected to a campus network of entrepreneurial seminars, classes, and events. Visit some of these sites to get a feel for some of the campus partners we will be working with when you arrive:\n\n* Insite\n* Transcend\n* Weinert Center for Entrepreneurship\n* Discovery to Product\n\nOur E-ship community includes faculty, students, business leaders, and campus partners. You can have access to our rich professional network by joining StartUp.\n\n### Law & Entrepreneurship Clinic\n\nThe UW-Madison Law School’s *Law & Entrepreneurship Clinic* provides free legal services to help entrepreneurs and small business owners realize their potential.\n\nBack to top\nBack to top\n\n## StartUp Professional Staff\n\nLoading…\n\nBack to top\nBack to top", "char_len": 908, "id": 11, "source": "Startup Learning Community", "type": "static_html", "category": "campus-portal", "url": "https://www.housing.wisc.edu/undergraduate/communities/startup/"}
{"chunk_id": "strato-vc::0", "doc_slug": "strato-vc", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "## [page] https://stratovc.com\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/5d9b3f78-b0fb-437e-b325-d58e6bc01ea4/highend-photography-earth-as-seen-from-international-space-station.jpg)\n\n# Strato VC\n\n### For Students, By Students\n\nBridging the gap between institutional investors and student founders.\n\nNEED FEEDBACK?\n\nSHARE YOUR IDEA!\n\n## **Our Mission**\n\nStrato VC is a student-led venture capital firm investing in undergraduate entrepreneurs with idea-stage companies. We provide mentorship, capital, and a network to help student founders turn ideas into real businesses.\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/1e714696-a059-472f-95f0-2607708dfcca/modern-business-building-scenery-touching-sky.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/bf2aa130-da1f-4fb0-891b-28a2c701d69c/vertical-low-angle-shot-high-rise-skyscrapers-glass-facade-frankfurt-germany.jpg)\n\n#\n\n#\n\n## **Investment Criteria**\n\n### 1.\n\n**STUDENT FOUNDERS**\n\nAll founders must be undergraduate students at UW–Madison.\n\n### 2.\n\n**IDEA STAGE**\n\nNo formal company incorporation required.\n\n### 3.\n\n**FUNDING**\n\nWe utilize a $30K investment per startup.\n\n### 4.\n\n**EXIT POTENTIAL**\n\nStartups should have an exit timeline of 3–5 years.\n\n#\n\n#\n\n## Why Strato VC?\n\n## 1.\n\n**STUDENTS**\n\nBuilt from the ground up with the needs of student entrepreneurs in mind.\n\n## 2.\n\n**MENTORSHIP**\n\nConnects founders with a diverse network of accomplished industry professionals.\n\n## 3.\n\n**ENTREPRENEURSHIP**\n\nLaunching the next generation of Wisconsin’s founders.\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/0466f0d4-23e7-4728-823d-0e5c96156ba2/observation-urban-building-business-steel.jpg)\n\n**CONNECT WITH STRATO VC**\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/c8e520f3-ed67-4291-aa74-97f325b747e8/view-futuristic-space-rocket.jpg)\n\n## [page] https://stratovc.com/about", "char_len": 1985, "id": 15, "source": "StratoVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://stratovc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "strato-vc::1", "doc_slug": "strato-vc", "chunk_index": 1, "text": "WITH STRATO VC**\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/c8e520f3-ed67-4291-aa74-97f325b747e8/view-futuristic-space-rocket.jpg)\n\n## [page] https://stratovc.com/about\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/1725572609365-W1YJCT14A53ZFS9U544A/unsplash-image-dzACSA_gShg.jpg)\n\n# REal Analysis. Real Investments. Real GROWTH.\n\n## About.\n\n### Strato VC is organized and operated for students, by students.\n\n### Members work closely with undergraduate founders to develop their business ideas though capital investments and mentorship.\n\n### Resources for Students prepare them for a career in entrepreneurship.\n\n---\n\n```\nStrato VC was founded in 2023 by a group of undergraduates who wanted to learn about venture capital and educate their peers about the dynamic industry. Recognizing the untapped talent of student entrepreneurs in Madison, Wisconsin, and their lack of access to institutional investment resources, the Strato team moved toward acquiring capital of its own.\n```\n\n```\nLaunched in the fall of 2025, Strato VC’s investment fund tasked itself with identifying and supporting student-led startups. Along with the capital needed to get a business off the ground, Strato VC connects student founders with its robust network of mentors and offers strategic industry insights for inexperienced entrepreneurs.\n```\n\n```\nAs a student run organization, Strato VC members are meant to learn alongside the students they support. The work they do in sourcing and due diligence prepares them with real world experience for a career in VC or any finance-related field.\n```\n\n```\nOur mission is to bridge the gap between students with high-potential ideas and resources that can help them achieve success. Strato VC seeks to grow Wisconsin’s startup ecosystem by empowering the next generation of entrepreneurs. The firm is the first in Wisconsin committed to investing in undergraduate founders’ ideas.\n```\n\nShare Your Idea\n\n## [page] https://stratovc.com/sourcing\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/0abcee79-db62-463b-8535-feec90cc72fa/cosmic-view-galaxy-space-scene.jpg)\n\n## Strato VC Sourcing", "char_len": 2202, "id": 15, "source": "StratoVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://stratovc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "strato-vc::2", "doc_slug": "strato-vc", "chunk_index": 2, "text": "committed to investing in undergraduate founders’ ideas.\n```\n\nShare Your Idea\n\n## [page] https://stratovc.com/sourcing\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/0abcee79-db62-463b-8535-feec90cc72fa/cosmic-view-galaxy-space-scene.jpg)\n\n## Strato VC Sourcing\n\nThe Strato VC Sourcing Team is busy connecting with Wisconsin's student founders. Recent deal flow has connected Strato Analysts with a number of founders in Madison.\n\nAs we continue our sourcing and diligence processes, we look forward to making our first round of investments.\n\nIf you’re an undergraduate with an idea for a company, we’d love to hear from you! To get in touch with our sourcing team, click the button below!\n\nStrato VC Sourcing Form\n\n## [page] https://stratovc.com/team\n\n# Our Team\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/b925e269-b484-4905-a799-04ce1aa489c5/Strato+VC+2026-19.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/382ac7b9-6386-4d7c-9603-d470f2024d87/Strato+VC+2026-2.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/43c2e380-0575-45e3-afbe-bc3449b005c7/Strato+VC+2026-14.jpg)\n\n**James O’Toole**\n\nPartner\n\n**Romeo Trikolas**\n\nManaging Partner\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/6595d65f-13c9-4ccb-8f67-cfe2756d7277/Strato+VC+2026-16.jpg)\n\n**Shradha Godishala**\n\nPartner\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/cf1f8bf5-e151-4ce7-8bd5-f8ddc8893769/Strato+VC+2026-8.jpg)\n\n**Ryan Arkeh**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/0c356df7-57e3-45ce-a753-a67d4cabf353/25-0-0_StratoVC+Team-13.jpg)\n\n**Akshad Surve**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/73df77d9-1fab-4908-b9f2-24294d3b87b0/Strato+VC+2026-18.jpg)\n\n**Lorenzo de Simone**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/2089ca3d-e733-4898-9f03-5119479ff4f8/Strato+VC+2026-6.jpg)\n\n**Cade Thayer**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/244f85e0-2082-4ded-8406-7eedeee0c681/25-0-0_StratoVC+Team-15.jpg)", "char_len": 2273, "id": 15, "source": "StratoVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://stratovc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "strato-vc::3", "doc_slug": "strato-vc", "chunk_index": 3, "text": "Thayer**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/244f85e0-2082-4ded-8406-7eedeee0c681/25-0-0_StratoVC+Team-15.jpg)\n\n**Praveer Tiwari**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/33182be0-1504-4046-b31d-c933151e9b0b/Strato+VC+2026-10.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/6ba06bd0-edf7-40bf-aca1-e053f58a899b/Facetune_21-02-2026-17-24-39.jpeg)\n\n**Kai Dunham**\n\n```\nAnalyst\n```\n\n**Abiir Godbole**\n\n```\nAnalyst\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/b9a7098f-eb6d-439d-bf15-e10a355c85e1/Strato+VC+2026-4.jpg)\n\n**Elijah Gudmestad**\n\n```\nAnalyst\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/1328c361-a155-4cb9-a14b-e07fa163b773/Strato+VC+2026-12.jpg)\n\n**Michael Singer**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/6f86c01c-c0cf-4d5c-87eb-488d6885d07e/Atmosphere_-_2+2.jpg)\n\n## Connect with Us\n\nGet In Touch!\n\n## [page] https://stratovc.com/connect\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/2bcd8089-5aa5-4a45-8068-b93aec75e2b4/future-visions-business-technology-concept.jpg)\n\n## Connect With Us\n\n## EVents\n\nNEED FEEDBACK?\n\nSHARE YOUR IDEA!\n\n## Contact Us\n\n## [page] http://stratovc.com\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/5d9b3f78-b0fb-437e-b325-d58e6bc01ea4/highend-photography-earth-as-seen-from-international-space-station.jpg)\n\n# Strato VC\n\n### For Students, By Students\n\nBridging the gap between institutional investors and student founders.\n\nNEED FEEDBACK?\n\nSHARE YOUR IDEA!\n\n## **Our Mission**\n\nStrato VC is a student-led venture capital firm investing in undergraduate entrepreneurs with idea-stage companies. We provide mentorship, capital, and a network to help student founders turn ideas into real businesses.\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/1e714696-a059-472f-95f0-2607708dfcca/modern-business-building-scenery-touching-sky.jpg)", "char_len": 2132, "id": 15, "source": "StratoVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://stratovc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "strato-vc::4", "doc_slug": "strato-vc", "chunk_index": 4, "text": "with idea-stage companies. We provide mentorship, capital, and a network to help student founders turn ideas into real businesses.\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/1e714696-a059-472f-95f0-2607708dfcca/modern-business-building-scenery-touching-sky.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/bf2aa130-da1f-4fb0-891b-28a2c701d69c/vertical-low-angle-shot-high-rise-skyscrapers-glass-facade-frankfurt-germany.jpg)\n\n#\n\n#\n\n## **Investment Criteria**\n\n### 1.\n\n**STUDENT FOUNDERS**\n\nAll founders must be undergraduate students at UW–Madison.\n\n### 2.\n\n**IDEA STAGE**\n\nNo formal company incorporation required.\n\n### 3.\n\n**FUNDING**\n\nWe utilize a $30K investment per startup.\n\n### 4.\n\n**EXIT POTENTIAL**\n\nStartups should have an exit timeline of 3–5 years.\n\n#\n\n#\n\n## Why Strato VC?\n\n## 1.\n\n**STUDENTS**\n\nBuilt from the ground up with the needs of student entrepreneurs in mind.\n\n## 2.\n\n**MENTORSHIP**\n\nConnects founders with a diverse network of accomplished industry professionals.\n\n## 3.\n\n**ENTREPRENEURSHIP**\n\nLaunching the next generation of Wisconsin’s founders.\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/0466f0d4-23e7-4728-823d-0e5c96156ba2/observation-urban-building-business-steel.jpg)\n\n**CONNECT WITH STRATO VC**\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/c8e520f3-ed67-4291-aa74-97f325b747e8/view-futuristic-space-rocket.jpg)\n\n## [page] http://stratovc.com/about\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/1725572609365-W1YJCT14A53ZFS9U544A/unsplash-image-dzACSA_gShg.jpg)\n\n# REal Analysis. Real Investments. Real GROWTH.\n\n## About.\n\n### Strato VC is organized and operated for students, by students.\n\n### Members work closely with undergraduate founders to develop their business ideas though capital investments and mentorship.\n\n### Resources for Students prepare them for a career in entrepreneurship.\n\n---", "char_len": 1988, "id": 15, "source": "StratoVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://stratovc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "strato-vc::5", "doc_slug": "strato-vc", "chunk_index": 5, "text": "GROWTH.\n\n## About.\n\n### Strato VC is organized and operated for students, by students.\n\n### Members work closely with undergraduate founders to develop their business ideas though capital investments and mentorship.\n\n### Resources for Students prepare them for a career in entrepreneurship.\n\n---\n\n```\nStrato VC was founded in 2023 by a group of undergraduates who wanted to learn about venture capital and educate their peers about the dynamic industry. Recognizing the untapped talent of student entrepreneurs in Madison, Wisconsin, and their lack of access to institutional investment resources, the Strato team moved toward acquiring capital of its own.\n```\n\n```\nLaunched in the fall of 2025, Strato VC’s investment fund tasked itself with identifying and supporting student-led startups. Along with the capital needed to get a business off the ground, Strato VC connects student founders with its robust network of mentors and offers strategic industry insights for inexperienced entrepreneurs.\n```\n\n```\nAs a student run organization, Strato VC members are meant to learn alongside the students they support. The work they do in sourcing and due diligence prepares them with real world experience for a career in VC or any finance-related field.\n```\n\n```\nOur mission is to bridge the gap between students with high-potential ideas and resources that can help them achieve success. Strato VC seeks to grow Wisconsin’s startup ecosystem by empowering the next generation of entrepreneurs. The firm is the first in Wisconsin committed to investing in undergraduate founders’ ideas.\n```\n\nShare Your Idea\n\n## [page] http://stratovc.com/sourcing\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/0abcee79-db62-463b-8535-feec90cc72fa/cosmic-view-galaxy-space-scene.jpg)\n\n## Strato VC Sourcing\n\nThe Strato VC Sourcing Team is busy connecting with Wisconsin's student founders. Recent deal flow has connected Strato Analysts with a number of founders in Madison.\n\nAs we continue our sourcing and diligence processes, we look forward to making our first round of investments.\n\nIf you’re an undergraduate with an idea for a company, we’d love to hear from you! To get in touch with our sourcing team, click the button below!\n\nStrato VC Sourcing Form", "char_len": 2268, "id": 15, "source": "StratoVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://stratovc.com/"}
{"chunk_id": "strato-vc::6", "doc_slug": "strato-vc", "chunk_index": 6, "text": "in Madison.\n\nAs we continue our sourcing and diligence processes, we look forward to making our first round of investments.\n\nIf you’re an undergraduate with an idea for a company, we’d love to hear from you! To get in touch with our sourcing team, click the button below!\n\nStrato VC Sourcing Form\n\n## [page] http://stratovc.com/team\n\n# Our Team\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/b925e269-b484-4905-a799-04ce1aa489c5/Strato+VC+2026-19.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/382ac7b9-6386-4d7c-9603-d470f2024d87/Strato+VC+2026-2.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/43c2e380-0575-45e3-afbe-bc3449b005c7/Strato+VC+2026-14.jpg)\n\n**James O’Toole**\n\nPartner\n\n**Romeo Trikolas**\n\nManaging Partner\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/6595d65f-13c9-4ccb-8f67-cfe2756d7277/Strato+VC+2026-16.jpg)\n\n**Shradha Godishala**\n\nPartner\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/cf1f8bf5-e151-4ce7-8bd5-f8ddc8893769/Strato+VC+2026-8.jpg)\n\n**Ryan Arkeh**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/0c356df7-57e3-45ce-a753-a67d4cabf353/25-0-0_StratoVC+Team-13.jpg)\n\n**Akshad Surve**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/73df77d9-1fab-4908-b9f2-24294d3b87b0/Strato+VC+2026-18.jpg)\n\n**Lorenzo de Simone**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/2089ca3d-e733-4898-9f03-5119479ff4f8/Strato+VC+2026-6.jpg)\n\n**Cade Thayer**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/244f85e0-2082-4ded-8406-7eedeee0c681/25-0-0_StratoVC+Team-15.jpg)\n\n**Praveer Tiwari**\n\n```\nAssociate\n```\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/33182be0-1504-4046-b31d-c933151e9b0b/Strato+VC+2026-10.jpg)\n\n![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/65b0762eeaf029284c0164d0/6ba06bd0-edf7-40bf-aca1-e053f58a899b/Facetune_21-02-2026-17-24-39.jpeg)\n\n**Kai Dunham**\n\n```\nAnalyst\n```\n\n**Abiir Godbole**\n\n```\nAnalyst\n```", "char_len": 2217, "id": 15, "source": "StratoVC", "type": "static_html", "category": "funding", "url": "https://stratovc.com/"}
