{"chunk_id": "tech-entrepreneurship-office::0", "doc_slug": "tech-entrepreneurship-office", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "## [page] https://teo.wisc.edu\n\n![Text 'From idea to startup to scale up' over an aerial view of UW-Madison campus](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/02/home_pathways-UW_frame2-768x734.png)\n\n## CREATING PATHWAYS TO SUCCESS\n\nUW–Madison faculty, staff, students, and alumni play a critical role in solving everyday challenges. And UW’s Technology Entrepreneurship Office (TEO) serves as a critical bridge for transforming your potential solutions into tangible technologies. As your ***dedicated partner*** across the full lifecycle, TEO offers networking opportunities, a mix of online and in-person courses, and ***tailored mentorship***, ensuring that every entrepreneur receives personalized 1:1 guidance unique to their specific needs. We help you navigate each stage of the startup journey with ***confidence.***\n\nGet started with TEO\n\n## What We Do\n\n![An icon of a lightbulb sits above the words accelerate technology transfer](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/04/column-header_tech-transfer-900x600.png)\n\nWe help evaluate the commercial potential of research outcomes to accelerate their transition to startups and established companies.\n\n![An icon of speech bubbles sits above text that reads make critical connections](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/04/column-header_connections-900x600.png)\n\nWe connect innovators with a broad entrepreneurial network, facilitating access to markets, investors, and opportunities.\n\n![An icon of four connected puzzles pieces sits above text that reads leverage essential resources](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/04/column-header_resources-900x600.png)\n\nWe boost technology commercialization by providing mentorship and entrepreneurial expertise, as well as access to capital.\n\n## Tap Into the NSF I-Corps Program", "char_len": 1850, "id": 3, "source": "Tech Entrepreneurship Office", "type": "static_html", "category": "campus-portal", "url": "https://teo.wisc.edu/"}
{"chunk_id": "tech-entrepreneurship-office::1", "doc_slug": "tech-entrepreneurship-office", "chunk_index": 1, "text": "that reads leverage essential resources](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/04/column-header_resources-900x600.png)\n\nWe boost technology commercialization by providing mentorship and entrepreneurial expertise, as well as access to capital.\n\n## Tap Into the NSF I-Corps Program\n\nTEO is UW’s gateway to the National Science Foundation (NSF) I-Corps™ program, a rigorous training experience that helps transform lab discoveries into market-ready technologies with a focus on societal impact. UW–Madison faculty, staff, and students can leverage TEO and Great Lakes Hub regional training to prepare for the national I-Corps competition. Watch the video to learn more.\n\n##### Learn more about I-Corps\n\n## Get Started with TEO\n\n![two overlapping talk bubbles framed in red](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/02/home_get-started-icons_L2-150x150.png)\n\nSchedule a Consultation\n\nEngage directly with TEO’s director for one-on-one guidance on transforming your research into impactful technological solutions.\n\n![a key icon framed in red](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/02/home_get-started-icons_C2-150x150.png)\n\nGain Essential Skills\n\nParticipate in TEO’s dynamic workshops, offering a blend of online and in-person learning, to gain insights and skills essential for research commercialization.\n\n![icon of a rocket ship launching into space framed in red](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/02/home_get-started-icons_R2-150x150.png)\n\nApply for I-Corps\n\nUtilize the skills and knowledge gained through TEO workshops and mentorship to fast-track your market success in the I-Corps program.\n\n## Upcoming Events and Latest Insights\n\n### Upcoming Events and Courses\n\n* Jun\n\n25\n\nFree Virtual Workshop: 2026 UW-Madison NSF I-Corps™ Summer Cohort\n  June 25, 2026 @ 4:45 pm - July 30, 2026 @ 7:00 pm\n  Virtual\n* Jul\n\n20\n\nTake Control of Your Career with a Personalized Roadmap\n  July 20, 2026 @ 5:00 pm - July 22, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n* Oct\n\n01\n\nFall 2026 NSF I-Corps™: Materials, Manufacturing & Energy in the Age of AI\n  October 1, 2026 @ 4:45 pm - November 12, 2026 @ 7:00 pm\n  Virtual\n\nMore events\nMore\n\n### Our News\n\n* #### I-Corps Alum Dr. Jiajie Sui is the Next-Gen Entrepreneur for Next-Gen Batteries", "char_len": 2274, "id": 3, "source": "Tech Entrepreneurship Office", "type": "static_html", "category": "campus-portal", "url": "https://teo.wisc.edu/"}
{"chunk_id": "tech-entrepreneurship-office::2", "doc_slug": "tech-entrepreneurship-office", "chunk_index": 2, "text": "- July 22, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n* Oct\n\n01\n\nFall 2026 NSF I-Corps™: Materials, Manufacturing & Energy in the Age of AI\n  October 1, 2026 @ 4:45 pm - November 12, 2026 @ 7:00 pm\n  Virtual\n\nMore events\nMore\n\n### Our News\n\n* #### I-Corps Alum Dr. Jiajie Sui is the Next-Gen Entrepreneur for Next-Gen Batteries\n\n\"Next-gen\" batteries are on the horizon, and NSF I-Corps alumna and Early Career Entrepreneur-in-Residence Jiajie Sui is helping to commercialize them.\n\nMarch 5, 2026\n* #### Leadership Spotlight: Oliver Wiener\n\nOliver Wiener is an entrepreneur and financier with expertise in the digital realm. He is the Founder and Managing Partner of Kensington Merchant Partners, an investment firm in the evolving financial and technological ecosystem. He was formerly a Portfolio …\n\nMarch 2, 2026\n* More News\n  More\n\n## [page] https://teo.wisc.edu/about\n\n## A catalyst for innovation at the University of Wisconsin–Madison\n\nEquipped with a team of seasoned experts, the Technology Entrepreneurship Office is uniquely positioned to provide one-on-one mentorship and tailored partnerships to facilitate the transformation of emerging innovations into tangible, commercially viable solutions.\n\nOur team also partners with the U.S. NSF I-Corps Great Lakes Region Hub and a diverse group of entrepreneurs to provide invaluable entrepreneurial training to UW-Madison researchers.\n\nMeet the Team\n\n## Staff Members\n\n![A mature white woman with dark hair and brown eyes](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/03/BB_red-frameAsset-3-400x400.png)\n\n### Bonnie Bachman\n\nPosition title: TEO Director and I-Corps Program Director\n\n* LinkedIn profile for Bonnie Bachman\n\n![Headshot of Asian woman with medium length red-brown hair, wearing a dark brown t-shirt and a gold necklace](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2024/03/shelley-headshot.png)\n\n### Xiaolei (Shelley) Shi\n\nPosition title: Program Specialist for Translational Research\n\n* LinkedIn profile for Xiaolei (Shelley) Shi\n\n## Students\n\n![](https://teo.wisc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/2156/2025/01/Fadhel_Headshot-400x400.png)\n\n### Fadhel Alrabiah\n\nPosition title: Startup Associate\n\n* LinkedIn profile for Fadhel Alrabiah\n\n## Advisory Board", "char_len": 2211, "id": 3, "source": "Tech Entrepreneurship Office", "type": "static_html", "category": "campus-portal", "url": "https://teo.wisc.edu/"}
